        NUMBER_FOUR_AYAME_PLANNED_THIS_OPERATION_SO_SHE                        = 7805,  -- Number Four, Ayame, planned this operation, so she will be in charge.
        NUMBER_FIVE_NAJI_WILL_BE_ASSISTING_HER_ALL                             = 7806,  -- Number Five, Naji, will be assisting her. All of you are to follow their orders during the operation. Ayame, if you please?
        FIRST_WE_ARE_TO_RENDEZVOUS_IN_BEADEAUX_NEAR                            = 7807,  -- First, we are to rendezvous in Beadeaux, near the entrance to the Quadav stronghold. Your targets are the Copper Quadav in charge of perimeter defense.
        EACH_OF_YOU_ARE_TO_DEFEAT_TWENTY_COPPER                                = 7808,  -- Each of you are to defeat twenty Copper Quadav. Once you have accomplished this objective, you are to disperse and retreat, then regroup at the entrance once again.
        DON_T_FORGET_THE_RENDEZVOUS_POINT_IS_RIGHT                             = 7809,  -- Don't forget, the rendezvous point is right inside Beadeaux! Nobody get lost, now!
        YOU_SHOULD_TALK_YOU_D_EVEN_GET_LOST                                    = 7810,  -- You should talk. You'd even get lost in your own Mog House.
        ONCE_YOU_ARE_PREPARED_WASTE_NO_TIME_GOING                              = 7811,  -- Once you are prepared, waste no time going to the rendezvous point. Dismissed.
        THE_WAY_TO_THE_RENDEZVOUS_POINT_IS_THROUGH                             = 7812,  -- The way to the rendezvous point is through the Pashhow Marshlands. It is right inside Beadeaux.
        WALK_ACROSS_THE_PASHHOW_MARSHLANDS_TO_GET_TO                           = 7813,  -- Walk across the Pashhow Marshlands to get to the rendezvous point. It's right inside Beadeaux. Make sure to bring everything you'll need!
        THE_RENDEZVOUS_POINT_IS_ACROSS_THE_PASHHOW_MARSHLANDS                  = 7814,  -- The rendezvous point is across the Pashhow Marshlands, and right inside Beadeaux. Be prepared for anything.
        AH_YOU_ARE_HERE_GOOD                                                   = 7815,  -- Ah, you are here. Good.
        YOU_MUST_HAVE_HEARD_THIS_ALREADY_BUT_WE                                = 7816,  -- You must have heard this already, but we need someone reliable to take on missions centered around our embassy in Jeuno.
        I_VE_TALKED_TO_BOTH_THE_PRESIDENT_AND                                  = 7817,  -- I've talked to both the president and Captain Volker, and it is our unanimous opinion that you are the only person adequate for the task.
        WE_WILL_GIVE_YOU_A_LETTER_OF_INTRODUCTION                              = 7818,  -- We will give you a letter of introduction, which you will present at our embassy in Jeuno to receive further instructions.
        HANS_THE_LETTER                                                        = 7819,  -- Hans, the letter.
        YES_SIR_HERE_YOU_GO                                                    = 7820,  -- Yes, sir. Here you go.
        GOOD_LUCK_I_AM_COUNTING_ON_YOU                                         = 7821,  -- Good luck. I am counting on you.
        YOU_RE_BACK_FROM_JEUNO_NO_TIME_TO                                      = 7822,  -- You're back from Jeuno. No time to chat. Come with me.
        YOU_SAY_SOMEONE_SNUCK_A_FAMILIAR_INTO_THE                              = 7823,  -- You say someone snuck a familiar into the President's Office, but you were not warned of its presence?
        YES_SIR_WE_WERE_TAKEN_BY_SURPRISE_I                                    = 7824,  -- Yes, sir. We were taken by surprise. I did not think anything like this was possible...
        SIR_LUCIUS_DID_SEND_ME_A_REPORT_STATING                                = 7825,  -- Sir Lucius did send me a report stating that our magical defenses were inadequate, but I didn't think that they would be so easy to break...
        ID_7826                                                                = 7826,  -- ...
        FATHER                                                                 = 7827,  -- Father!?
        CORNELIA                                                               = 7828,  -- Cornelia...
        UNCLE_CID_WHERE_S_FATHER                                               = 7829,  -- Uncle Cid! Where's Father?
        CALM_DOWN_CORNELIA_WE_HAVE_THE_SITUATION_UNDER                         = 7830,  -- Calm down, Cornelia. We have the situation under control.
        IS_FATHER_PLEASE_TELL_ME_IT_S_NOT                                      = 7831,  -- Is Father...? Please, tell me it's not true...!
        HMPH_DON_T_MAKE_A_SCENE_I_M                                            = 7832,  -- Hmph. Don't make a scene. I'm not dead yet.
        FATHER_2                                                               = 7833,  -- Father!
        CORNELIA_THIS_DOES_NOT_CONCERN_YOU_GO_TO                               = 7834,  -- Cornelia, this does not concern you. Go to your room.
        LUCIUS_EXPLAIN_WHAT_HAPPENED                                           = 7835,  -- Lucius, explain what happened.
        THE_FAMILIAR_USED_MAGIC_TO_INFILTRATE_THE_BUILDING                     = 7836,  -- The familiar used magic to infiltrate the building...then it proceeded to cross the office straight toward the president's private chambers.
        FORTUNATELY_THE_PRESIDENT_WAS_AWAKE_AT_THE_TIME                        = 7837,  -- Fortunately, the president was awake at the time, and was not injured...
        BUT_THEY_TOOK_THE_TALISMAN                                             = 7838,  -- But they took the talisman.
        THE_TALISMAN_THE_KEY_TO_THE_SHADOW_LORD                                = 7839,  -- The talisman!? The key to the Shadow Lord's seal!?
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_OUR_ALLIED_FORCES_DEFEATED_THE                        = 7840,  -- Twenty years ago, our allied forces defeated the Shadow Lord in the Northlands and sealed him away from our world. Chief Cid and Captain Volker were there, I believe.
        THE_THREE_PARTS_OF_THE_KEY_TO_THE                                      = 7841,  -- The three parts of the key to the seal, the talismans, were given to each nation's leader for safekeeping. But now, at least one of them is gone...
        WHO_WOULD_DO_SUCH_A_THING                                              = 7842,  -- Who would do such a thing?
        HAVE_YOU_NOT_FOUND_THE_CULPRIT_YET_GRANTED                             = 7843,  -- Have you not found the culprit yet? Granted, there are many who bear ill feelings towards me...
        BUT_THEN_AGAIN_THOSE_FOOLS_IN_THE_SENATE                               = 7844,  -- But then again, those fools in the Senate are too busy squabbling with each other, and the Galka rebels are too savage to possess any magic skills...
        ID_7845                                                                = 7845,  -- ...
        FATHER_DON_T_TALK_ABOUT_THE_GALKA_THAT                                 = 7846,  -- Father! Don't talk about the Galka that way!
        WHY_ARE_YOU_STILL_HERE_DID_I_NOT                                       = 7847,  -- Why are you still here? Did I not tell you to go to your room?
        ID_7848                                                                = 7848,  -- ...
        FROM_THE_REPORTS_WE_HAVE_RECEIVED_FROM_THE                             = 7849,  -- From the reports we have received from the other nations, we must assume that the Kindred are trying to bring the Shadow Lord back.
        THEN_WE_MUST_GO_TO_THE_NORTHLANDS_TO                                   = 7850,  -- Then we must go to the Northlands to investigate!
        THE_SENATE_WOULD_HAVE_TO_APPROVE_BEFORE_I                              = 7851,  -- The Senate would have to approve before I can let the Mythril Musketeers go so far away from the city.
        IT_WOULD_TAKE_TOO_MUCH_TIME_AND_TIME                                   = 7852,  -- It would take too much time, and time is a luxury we cannot afford. Besides, the Senate has no sense of crisis--they would just reject my proposal.
        THEN                                                                   = 7853,  -- Then...
        WE_HAVE_TO_FIND_SOMEONE_WITH_NO_LEGAL                                  = 7854,  -- We have to find someone with no legal constraints.
        I_AM_ASSIGNING_YOU_A_MISSION_ADVENTURER_AND                            = 7855,  -- I am assigning you a mission, adventurer, and putting you under the Musketeers' jurisdiction.
        YOU_DO_NOT_HAVE_TO_ANSWER_RIGHT_AWAY                                   = 7856,  -- You do not have to answer right away, but do you accept?
        ACCEPT_THE_MISSION_YES_I_NEED_SOME_TIME                                = 7857,  -- Accept the mission? Yes. I need some time.
        THEN_LET_US_TALK_IN_PRIVATE_VOLKER_COME                                = 7858,  -- Then let us talk in private. Volker, come with us.
        VERY_WELL_TALK_TO_THE_GUARD_IN_CHARGE                                  = 7859,  -- Very well. Talk to the guard in charge of missions when you feel you are ready.
        I_HEAR_YOU_ACCEPTED_THE_MISSION_COME_WITH                              = 7860,  -- I hear you accepted the mission. Come with me.
        FIRST_LET_ME_TELL_YOU_ABOUT_YOUR_DESTINATION                           = 7861,  -- First, let me tell you about your destination. You are to journey to the cursed Northlands, to the ruins of Fei'Yin. You will find the ruins at the northeastern corner of the Beaucedine Glacier.
        THE_CITY_OF_FEI_YIN_WAS_BUILT_IN                                       = 7862,  -- The city of Fei'Yin was built in ancient times by a civilization far more advanced than ours.
        WE_BELIEVE_THEY_CALLED_THEMSELVES_THE_ZILART_THERE                     = 7863,  -- We believe they called themselves the Zilart. There are many other ruins in Vana'diel thought to be of their making.
        CONSIDERING_HOW_LONG_AGO_THEY_WERE_BUILT_THEIR                         = 7864,  -- Considering how long ago they were built, their state of preservation is astounding. It is as if they are protected by some unseen force that defies time itself.
        THIRTY_YEARS_AGO_A_MULTINATIONAL_TEAM_WAS_SENT                         = 7865,  -- Thirty years ago, a multinational team was sent to the Northlands to try to uncover the secrets of the Zilart's power.
        ULRICH_VOLKER_S_UNCLE_AND_THE_CAPTAIN_OF                               = 7866,  -- Ulrich, Volker's uncle--and the captain of the Mythril Musketeers at the time--led the Bastokan contingent of that expedition.
        UNFORTUNATELY_THEY_CAME_BACK_EMPTY_HANDED                              = 7867,  -- Unfortunately, they came back empty-handed.
        ID_7868                                                                = 7868,  -- ...
        CAPTAIN_VOLKER_WILL_TELL_YOU_THE_WAY_TO                                = 7869,  -- Captain Volker will tell you the way to your destination. He undertook the same journey twenty years ago, near the end of the Great War.
        EVEN_BEFORE_THE_WAR_FEI_YIN_WAS_OVERRUN                                = 7870,  -- Even before the war, Fei'Yin was overrun with fiends. We captured it from the Shadow Lord at the cost of many lives.
        AFTER_THE_WAR_WE_SET_SEALS_ON_BOTH                                     = 7871,  -- After the war, we set seals on both sides of the border to keep the Shadow Lord's minions at bay. One seal in the ruined coliseum on the inside, and another in Fei'Yin on the outside.
        THAT_WAS_TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_IN_THOSE_DAYS                                = 7872,  -- That was twenty years ago. In those days, we could reach the Beaucedine Glacier from East Ronfaure through Ranguemont Pass.
        THAT_IS_STILL_THE_ONLY_WAY_THERE_BUT                                   = 7873,  -- That is still the only way there, but I believe San d'Oria is guarding that road now. You will have to find some way through.
        YOUR_OBJECTIVE_IS_TO_ASCERTAIN_THAT_THE_SEAL                           = 7874,  -- Your objective is to ascertain that the seal in Fei'Yin is still intact. If it is not, replace it with the one we will be providing you.
        YOU_DO_HAVE_AN_AIRSHIP_PASS_DO_YOU                                     = 7875,  -- You do have an airship pass, do you not?
        HEAD_TO_JEUNO_AND_TAKE_THE_FLIGHT_TO                                   = 7876,  -- Head to Jeuno, and take the flight to San d'Oria as soon as possible. You are dismissed.
        WHOA_YOU_MADE_IT_BACK_FROM_FEI_YIN                                     = 7877,  -- Whoa! You made it back from Fei'Yin in one piece! Come with me, quick!
        SO_THE_SEAL_IN_FEI_YIN_WAS_ALSO                                        = 7878,  -- So...the seal in Fei'Yin was also broken.
        WHERE_WERE_THE_SAN_D_ORIANS_IT_WAS                                     = 7879,  -- Where were the San d'Orians!? It was their duty to protect it!
        MISTER_PRESIDENT_SHOULD_WE_ASK_THE_SENATE_ABOUT                        = 7880,  -- Mister President? Should we ask the Senate about an incursion to Zvahl?
        WE_SEEM_TO_HAVE_NO_OTHER_CHOICE_BUT                                    = 7881,  -- We seem to have no other choice. But until they come to a decision, our hands are tied.
        WE_WOULD_LIKE_YOU_TO_STAND_BY_FOR                                      = 7882,  -- We would like you to stand by for further orders. We have preparations to make.
        I_HEARD_YOU_MENTION_MEETING_A_GALKA_DRESSED                            = 7883,  -- I heard you mention meeting a Galka dressed all in black in Fei'Yin. Tell me more about him.
        AS_I_THOUGHT_IT_IS_ZEID_THEN_HE                                        = 7884,  -- As I thought...it is Zeid. Then he has been tracking the Kindred ever since he disappeared twenty years ago.
        HE_WAS_THE_NUMBER_TWO_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_THE                            = 7885,  -- He was the Number Two Mythril Musketeer--the Galka named War Cloud. Ah...but he never liked being called by his Hume-given name.
        HE_IS_THE_ONE_WHO_DEFEATED_THE_SHADOW                                  = 7886,  -- He is the one who defeated the Shadow Lord... He should have been Captain, not I.
        STILL_WHY_HAS_HE_BEEN_HIDING_FROM_US                                   = 7887,  -- Still, why has he been hiding from us? What is there in the Northlands that would change Zeid, and even my uncle, so much?
        AH_I_APOLOGIZE_IT_IS_NOT_MY_PLACE                                      = 7888,  -- Ah, I apologize. It is not my place to ask these questions. I am but a Musketeer, a humble soldier of Bastok.
        HUH_NO_THIS_ISN_T_THE_BLACKSMITHS_GUILD                                = 7889,  -- Huh? No, this isn't the Blacksmiths' Guild. That's to the northwest.
        HEY_YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_RIGHT_I_NEED                                  = 7890,  -- Hey, you're an adventurer, right? I need % for one of my experiments.
        CAN_YOU_GET_ME_SOME_I_VE_HEARD                                         = 7891,  -- Can you get me some? I've heard they appear during dust storms...
        GO_ASK_DRANGORD_THE_GALKA_HE_SAID_HE                                   = 7892,  -- Go ask Drangord the Galka. He said he found some during his adventuring years.
        THANKS_THIS_WILL_HELP_ME_WITH_MY_EXPERIMENTS                           = 7893,  -- %! Thanks, this will help me with my experiments! But I can always use more if you happen to come upon additional quantities.
        HMM_THIS_MACHINE_S_BEEN_ACTING_UP_LATELY                               = 7894,  -- Hmm...this machine's been acting up lately. I wonder if the oil's gone bad...
        THIS_MACHINE_NEEDS_OILING_BUT_WE_RE_ALL                                = 7895,  -- This machine needs oiling, but we're all out of machine oil. What could I use as a substitute, I wonder?
        OF_COURSE_WHY_DIDN_T_I_THINK_OF                                        = 7896,  -- %? Of course! Why didn't I think of that? Thank you. Here, take this as payment.
        MY_JOB_S_NOT_THAT_BAD_REALLY_WORKING                                   = 7897,  -- My job's not that bad, really. Working with machines beats working in the mines any day.
        DESIGNING_NEW_PRODUCTS_ISN_T_EASY_I_DON                                = 7898,  -- Designing new products isn't easy. I don't know how Chief Cid does it, coming up with new inventions almost every week.
        TO_BE_HONEST_IT_S_NOT_ALWAYS_EASY                                      = 7899,  -- To be honest, it's not always easy working with Humes, but you get used to it. You have to.
        YOU_VE_GOT_TO_BE_FLEXIBLE_YOU_KNOW                                     = 7900,  -- You've got to be flexible, you know? You gotta keep up with the times. Otherwise you'll end up in the mines with the rest of the old, hard-headed Galka.
        THIS_IS_THE_DARKSTEEL_FORGE_YOU_MUST_VE                                = 7901,  -- This is the Darksteel Forge. You must've heard of darksteel before.
        DARKSTEEL_IS_AN_ALLOY_HARDER_YET_MORE_FLEXIBLE                         = 7902,  -- Darksteel is an alloy harder yet more flexible than regular steel. What's more, it neither stains nor rusts. The only drawback is that it's a little heavy.
        ITS_FORMULA_WAS_A_GALKAN_SECRET_FOR_A                                  = 7903,  -- Its formula was a Galkan secret for a long time, but lately we've decided to teach Humes how to make it, too.
        KNOWING_HUMES_THOUGH_THEY_WOULD_VE_FIGURED_IT                          = 7904,  -- Knowing Humes, though, they would've figured it out eventually, and come up with something better.
        CAN_I_HELP_YOU_THIS_IS_THE_CERMET                                      = 7905,  -- Can I help you? This is the Cermet Refinery. Normally, only factory workers are allowed in, but...
        WELL_I_GUESS_YOU_RE_OKAY_DO_YOU                                        = 7906,  -- Well, I guess you're okay. Do you know what cermet is? It's an alloy that's harder and lighter than steel, doesn't rust, and can withstand extreme heat. Amazing, isn't it?
        IT_S_THE_BYPRODUCT_OF_RECENT_BREAKTHROUGHS_IN                          = 7907,  -- It's the byproduct of recent breakthroughs in alchemy. Thanks to cermet, Chief Cid's engine designs are now years ahead of their time!
        IN_FACT_CERMET_AH_NO_I_CAN_T                                           = 7908,  -- In fact, cermet...ah, no, I can't tell you any more. Just that...if we manage to find a way to cut down its production cost, we can put those Galka smiths on the spot!
        THIS_IS_THE_CERMET_REFINERY_THE_FACTORY_IS                             = 7909,  -- This is the Cermet Refinery. The factory is off-limits to unauthorized personnel.
        THEN_AGAIN_EVEN_IF_THOSE_ANACHRONISTIC_SAN_D                           = 7910,  -- Then again, even if those anachronistic San d'Orians did manage to get in, they probably wouldn't be able to make heads or tails out of our instruments!
        THE_YOUNGER_GALKA_WHO_WORK_HERE_ANSWER_TO                              = 7911,  -- The younger Galka who work here answer to their Hume-given names, like pets to their master! Have they no shame!?
        IT_IS_ALL_BECAUSE_OF_THE_LOSS_OF                                       = 7912,  -- It is all because of the loss of our Talekeeper. If only Sir Raogrimm were here...
        I_VE_HEARD_GOOD_THINGS_ABOUT_YOU_IT                                    = 7913,  -- I've heard good things about you. It seems you're quite the adventurer now. I have a job for you.
        IT_S_WELL_IT_S_NOT_A_MISSION                                           = 7914,  -- It's...well, it's not a mission, or anything official. Just a personal favor.
        THERE_S_A_TAVERN_IN_THE_PORT_DISTRICT                                  = 7915,  -- There's a tavern in the Port District called the Steaming Sheep Restaurant. I want you to go see if the matron there needs any help.
        AND_IF_SHE_DOES_COULD_YOU_TRY_TO                                       = 7916,  -- And if she does, could you try to help her? Of course, I will reward you for your services.
        HUH_I_THINK_A_CERTAIN_CRAWLER_IN_THE                                   = 7917,  -- %, huh? I think a certain crawler in the Crawlers' Nest drops them. Of course, you'll have to lure it out and defeat it first.
        AND_TO_LURE_IT_OUT_YOU_LL_NEED                                         = 7918,  -- And to lure it out, you'll need to use %.
        A_LETTER                                                               = 7919,  -- A letter?
        ID_7920                                                                = 7920,  -- ...
        I_I_SEE_MS_HILDA_SAID_THAT_HUH                                         = 7921,  -- I-I see. Ms. Hilda said that, huh? But I didn't mean to--no, never mind. You've done what I asked. I'll give you a reward.
        BUT_PLEASE_DON_T_TELL_ANYONE_ABOUT_THIS                                = 7922,  -- But please, don't tell anyone about this. Especially not Raibaht.
        DID_YOU_SAY_SOMETHING_CHIEF                                            = 7923,  -- Did you say something, Chief?
        GAH_DON_T_WASTE_TIME_TALKING_GET_BACK                                  = 7924,  -- Gah! Don't waste time talking! Get back to work!
        AN_INVITATION_FROM_THE_STEAMING_SHEEP_HMM_PLEASE                       = 7925,  -- An invitation from the Steaming Sheep? Hmm... Please do not mention this to the Chief. But tell the proprietor I will go visit her establishment as soon as I can.
        GOOD_OF_YOU_TO_COME_THE_REASON_WHY                                     = 7926,  -- Good of you to come. The reason why I didn't have Naji or Iron Eater bring you here is because the secrecy of this mission is paramount.
        VOLKER_WILL_SOON_JOIN_US_LET_US_TALK                                   = 7927,  -- Volker will soon join us. Let us talk in my private chambers. Come.
        GALINA_TELL_VOLKER_TO_COME_TO_MY_PRIVATE                               = 7928,  -- Galina, tell Volker to come to my private chambers when he arrives.
        WE_COULD_NOT_GET_THE_SENATE_S_APPROVAL                                 = 7929,  -- We could not get the Senate's approval. The Musketeers won't be allowed to leave the city gates. Those fools think that Bastok should not get itself involved...
        LET_SAN_D_ORIA_DEAL_WITH_THE_NORTHLANDS                                = 7930,  -- Let San d'Oria deal with the Northlands, they said! What do they think the Musketeers are for!? Surely they don't intend to use them in another war with San d'Oria!
        I_ADMIT_THAT_BASTOK_WOULD_DO_ANYTHING_FOR                              = 7931,  -- I admit that Bastok would do anything for its own gain. That is how we have come so far--myself as well.
        BASTOK_S_SUCCESS_IS_A_RESULT_OF_AGGRESSION                             = 7932,  -- Bastok's success is a result of aggression and initiative. But with the Senate dawdling so, we may pay dearly for our lack of action.
        REMEMBER_ONE_THING_YOU_ARE_AN_ADVENTURER_NOT                           = 7933,  -- Remember one thing: you are an adventurer, not a hero. You have no duty to the majority--especially one that chooses to stay idle at a time like this.
        GO_ON_THIS_MISSION_FOR_YOUR_OWN_GAIN                                   = 7934,  -- Go on this mission for your own gain. That is the Bastokan way. Do not concern yourself with responsibility--let a certain president and a Musketeer captain worry about that.
        VOLKER_COME                                                            = 7935,  -- Volker. Come.
        TELL_THE_ADVENTURER_WHAT_YOU_KNOW_OF_CASTLE                            = 7936,  -- Tell the adventurer what you know of Castle Zvahl. We do not have much time. Be brief.
        CROSS_THE_BEAUCEDINE_GLACIER_TO_THE_NORTHERNMOST_CORNER                = 7937,  -- Cross the Beaucedine Glacier to the northernmost corner of Quon, the frozen land of Xarcabard.
        THERE_YOU_WILL_FIND_CASTLE_ZVAHL_THE_KINDRED                           = 7938,  -- There you will find Castle Zvahl, the Kindred's stronghold. That is where our allied forces defeated the Shadow Lord twenty years ago.
        BUT_NOW_SOMEONE_IS_TRYING_TO_BRING_THE                                 = 7939,  -- But now, someone is trying to bring the Shadow Lord back. We must stop them, no matter what the cost.
        IF_YOU_ARE_TOO_LATE_AND_THEY_SUCCEED                                   = 7940,  -- If you are too late, and they succeed...you and your friends must try to defeat the Shadow Lord yourselves, as Cid, Zeid, and I once did.
        YOU_ADVENTURERS_HOLD_THE_FUTURE_OF_VANA_DIEL                           = 7941,  -- You adventurers hold the future of Vana'diel in your hands. We cannot accompany you, but our hopes and hearts go with you.
        GO_FINISH_YOUR_PREPARATIONS_AND_LEAVE_AS_SOON                          = 7942,  -- Go finish your preparations and leave as soon as possible. You are dismissed.
        WAIT_IF_YOU_SEE_ZEID_TELL_HIM_THAT                                     = 7943,  -- Wait... If you see Zeid, tell him that he has yet to best me in a fight...and that he should come back and challenge me.
        YOU_VE_DONE_IT_YOU_STOPPED_THEM_FROM                                   = 7944,  -- You've done it! You stopped them from bringing back the Shadow Lord!?
        WHAT_ARE_YOU_TALKING_ABOUT_VOLKER_THEY_PROBABLY                        = 7945,  -- What are you talking about, Volker? They probably defeated him and sent him back where he belongs! Am I right?
        WHAT_DEFEAT_HIM_BUT_THAT_S                                             = 7946,  -- What? Defeat him? But that's...
        IMPOSSIBLE_YOU_FIND_IT_HARD_TO_BELIEVE_THAT                            = 7947,  -- Impossible? You find it hard to believe that some adventurer could defeat the Shadow Lord, Captain? Have you not heard what the townspeople are saying?
        THEY_RE_SAYING_THE_AGE_OF_THE_ADVENTURERS                              = 7948,  -- They're saying the Age of the Adventurers has come!
        HMPH_ONLY_HISTORIANS_IN_POSTERITY_HAVE_THE_PRIVILEGE                   = 7949,  -- Hmph. Only historians, in posterity, have the privilege of saying such things.
        AND_IT_DOES_NOT_MATTER_IF_THEY_ONLY                                    = 7950,  -- And it does not matter if they only stopped the Shadow Lord from returning, or if they actually defeated him.
        THE_IMPORTANT_THING_IS_THAT_THEY_KEPT_THE                              = 7951,  -- The important thing is that they kept the Kindred from gaining power. And that, I believe, deserves a reward.
        GOOD_WORK_I_AM_RAISING_YOUR_RANK_AND                                   = 7952,  -- Good work. I am raising your rank. And here is your well-deserved reward.
        THE_SHADOW_LORD_MAY_HAVE_BEEN_VANQUISHED_AGAIN                         = 7953,  -- The Shadow Lord may have been vanquished again, but the Kindred are far from defeated. I have received reports of strange goings-on in the beastmen's strongholds.
        YOU_VE_PROBABLY_HEARD_THIS_TOO_MANY_TIMES                              = 7954,  -- You've probably heard this too many times, but...we're counting on you.
        SO_THAT_WAS_WHO_THE_SHADOW_LORD_WAS                                    = 7955,  -- So that was who the Shadow Lord was... Zeid must have known, and that's probably why he went off on his own.
        DON_T_TELL_VOLKER_ABOUT_THIS_ULRICH_S                                  = 7956,  -- Don't tell Volker about this. Ulrich's fate should also be kept from him, too. He may not be able to accept it yet.
        HE_ADMIRED_HIS_GRANDFATHER_A_LOT_THAT_S                                = 7957,  -- He admired his grandfather a lot...that's why it pained him to hear people say that Volker, himself, only became Captain because Raogrimm was gone.
        I_KNOW_THAT_HIDING_THE_TRUTH_FROM_HIM                                  = 7958,  -- I know that hiding the truth from him is not a good thing, but most of us are not as strong as you. We need time to heal.
        SORRY_TO_INTERRUPT_WHAT_ARE_YOU_TWO_TALKING                            = 7959,  -- Sorry to interrupt. What are you two talking about?
        UH_JUST_SAYING_THAT_KARST_REALLY_HASN_T                                = 7960,  -- Uh...just saying that Karst really hasn't changed, even after all of this.
        YES_BUT_I_THINK_I_UNDERSTAND_HIM_BETTER                                = 7961,  -- Yes, but I think I understand him better now. I may have been judging him too harshly.
        SPEAKING_OF_WHICH_YOU_STILL_HAVE_NOT_TOLD                              = 7962,  -- Speaking of which...you still have not told us why you backed President Karst in the last elections, Chief.
        OH_THAT_WELL_FIFTEEN_YEARS_AGO_EVEN_AFTER                              = 7963,  -- Oh, that. Well... Fifteen years ago, even after I resigned my post as head of the Gunpowder Room, the Senate was still in chaos, trying to find more people to blame for the accident in Palborough.
        BUT_THERE_WAS_ONE_JUNIOR_SENATOR_THERE_WHO                             = 7964,  -- But there was one junior senator there who proposed we abandon Palborough and reopen the Zeruhn Mines. That junior senator was Karst.
        THE_MINERS_STOOD_TO_LOSE_A_LOT_BUT                                     = 7965,  -- The miners stood to lose a lot, but at the time, his proposal was Bastok's best bet. I'm an engineer, so I respect skill. And I felt that Karst's political skills could be trusted.
        AND_HE_S_A_REAL_BASTOKER_TOO_VERY                                      = 7966,  -- And he's a real Bastoker, too--very ambitious, and real easy to figure out. I can still remember the eager look on his face when he announced his proposal to the Senate!
        HAH_HAH_HAH                                                            = 7967,  -- Hah hah hah!
        LADY_CORNELIA_IS_NOT_HERE_AT_THE_MOMENT                                = 7968,  -- Lady Cornelia is not here at the moment. I hope she doesn't stay out too late...
        LADY_CORNELIA_IS_IN_HER_ROOM_DOING_HER                                 = 7969,  -- Lady Cornelia is in her room doing her studies. Please come back some other--
        I_VE_HAD_ENOUGH_OF_STUDYING_I_M                                        = 7970,  -- I've had enough of studying. I'm going out!
        MILADY_DON_T_OH_NOT_AGAIN                                              = 7971,  -- Milady, don't-- Oh, not again!
        WHY_MUST_SHE_BE_LIKE_THIS_IF_THE                                       = 7972,  -- Why must she be like this? If the First Lady were still alive, she would never have tolerated this kind of behavior!
        LADY_CORNELIA_IS_IN_HER_ROOM_DOING_HER_2                               = 7973,  -- Lady Cornelia is in her room doing her studies. For once, she isn't--
        NO_MILADY_NOT_THIS_TIME_THE_PRESIDENT_HAS                              = 7974,  -- No, Milady! Not this time! The president has given me strict orders not to let you out of your--
        HELLO_COME_IN                                                          = 7975,  -- Hello. Come in.
        OH_YOU_WERE_EXPECTING_A_GUEST_I_M                                      = 7976,  -- Oh, you were expecting a guest! I'm sorry, I thought you were trying to sneak out--
        WAIT_MILADY_NO_YOU_SHOULDN_T_BE_LETTING                                = 7977,  -- Wait, Milady, no! You shouldn't be letting some adventurer into your room! You know the kind of places they frequent! And it wouldn't be proper!
        OH_BROTHER_CAN_YOU_BELIEVE_HER_THIS_IS                                 = 7978,  -- Oh, brother... Can you believe her? This is what I have to put up with every day. I usually manage to sneak out, though.
        I_VE_BEEN_MEANING_TO_ASK_YOU_HAVE                                      = 7979,  -- I've been meaning to ask you--have you ever heard the story of Cornelia the Musketeer?
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_HEARD_OF_A_MUSKETEER_NAMED                               = 7980,  -- Have you ever heard of a Musketeer named Cornelia? Yes, I have. Who?
        CORNELIA_THE_MONK_WHO_BECAME_A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER                       = 7981,  -- Cornelia, the monk who became a Mythril Musketeer, is pretty famous. She helped all those in need, whether they were Galka or Hume, rich or poor.
        YOU_VE_NEVER_HEARD_OF_HER_SHE_WAS                                      = 7982,  -- You've never heard of her? She was a monk who became a Mythril Musketeer. She helped all those in need, Galka and Hume, rich and poor alike.
        IT_WAS_RUMORED_THAT_SHE_AND_TALEKEEPER_RAOGRIMM                        = 7983,  -- It was rumored that she and Talekeeper Raogrimm--the only Galka destined to have become a Musketeer Captain if he were still alive--were sharing a forbidden love...
        BUT_NO_ONE_KNOWS_IF_THAT_WAS_TRUE                                      = 7984,  -- But no one knows if that was true, since neither returned from their expedition to Xarcabard thirty years ago.
        MY_MOTHER_NAMED_ME_AFTER_HER_SHE_TOLD                                  = 7985,  -- My mother named me after her. She told me that she wanted me to grow up to be just like her--someone who would treat everyone equally, and loved by all.
        MAYBE_THAT_S_WHY_I_TRY_SO_HARD                                         = 7986,  -- Maybe that's why I try so hard to help the Galka...though even if I weren't named Cornelia, I wouldn't stand by and watch them be treated like they are.
        BUT_IT_S_NO_GOOD_YOU_VE_SEEN                                           = 7987,  -- But it's no good. You've seen it, too. I just can't seem to do anything right. I wish I were as strong and smart as Lady Cornelia...
        THIS_GALKA_CHILD_TOLD_ME_THE_OTHER_DAY                                 = 7988,  -- This Galka child told me the other day, Why are you trying so hard? What can you do, you're just a girl!
        MAYBE_HE_S_RIGHT_MAYBE_I_CAN_T                                         = 7989,  -- Maybe he's right. Maybe I can't change anything...
        NO_I_VE_GOT_TO_TRY_HARDER_I                                            = 7990,  -- No! I've got to try harder! I'll show that know-it-all, Gumbah, what I can do!
        I_M_SORRY_TO_LEAVE_YOU_LIKE_THIS                                       = 7991,  -- I'm sorry to leave you like this, but I've got to go!
        THESE_DOORS_LEAD_TO_THE_PRESIDENT_S_OFFICE_2                           = 7992,  -- These doors lead to the President's Office.
        ENTER_THE_PRESIDENT_S_OFFICE_YES_NO                                    = 7993,  -- Enter the President's Office? Yes. No.
        EXIT_THE_PRESIDENT_S_OFFICE_YES_NO                                     = 7994,  -- Exit the President's Office? Yes. No.
        I_AM_COMPILING_DATA_ON_THE_EFFECTS_OF                                  = 7995,  -- I am compiling data on the effects of Bastok's mining and industrial projects on the environment.
        THESE_WHEELS_ARE_ENOUGH_TO_POWER_BASTOK_NOW                            = 7996,  -- These wheels are enough to power Bastok now, but what will they do when the city's needs exceed the amount of energy they can produce?
        I_VE_HEARD_ADVENTURERS_SAY_THAT_THE_QUADAV                             = 7997,  -- I've heard adventurers say that the Quadav dumping of industrial waste has polluted Beadeaux and its surrounding areas.
        I_D_LIKE_TO_EXAMINE_SOME_OF_THAT                                       = 7998,  -- I'd like to examine some of that %. I've heard you can find some near their forges, and that it's also easier to spot on rainy days.
        AH_YOU_VE_BROUGHT_ME_SOME_OF_THE                                       = 7999,  -- Ah, you've brought me some of the % from Beadeaux I asked for! Thank you. This will help me in my research.
        HUME_SCIENTISTS_SAY_THEY_DON_T_GIVE_A                                  = 8000,  -- Hume scientists say they don't give a damn about the Quadav environment, but this may be of use to us in the future... Oh, I'm sorry, I didn't mean to gripe. Here, let me reward you.
        LOOK_AROUND_YOU_DO_YOU_SEE_WHAT_BASTOKAN                               = 8001,  -- Look around you. Do you see what Bastokan technology can do? This technology is what makes us better than San d'Oria or even Windurst.
        AND_THANKS_TO_THAT_TECHNOLOGY_I_CAN_LET                                = 8002,  -- And thanks to that technology, I can let the machines do the work while I sit here and do nothing all day!
        THIS_WATER_WHEEL_SQUARE_IS_THE_CENTER_OF                               = 8003,  -- This water wheel square is the center of Bastok. That building to the east is the President's Office.
        THE_PRESIDENTIAL_AIDE_S_OFFICE_IS_TO_THE                               = 8004,  -- The Presidential Aide's Office is to the southeast, while the consulates of Jeuno, Windurst, and San d'Oria are, respectively, to the northeast, northwest, and southwest of the square.
        IT_S_LOCKED                                                            = 8005,  -- It's locked.
        THAT_STAR_IS_HERE_NO_IT_S_IN                                           = 8006,  -- That star is here...no, it's in that constellation there... Hm? What am I doing? Oh, I'm trying to match real stars with the ones on this map, but it's not as easy as it looks.
        SAY_YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_AREN_T_YOU                                    = 8007,  -- Say, you're an adventurer, aren't you? You must've been to a lot of places, seen many different skies... Would you like to take a look?
        LOOK_AT_THE_STELLAR_MAP_YES_NO                                         = 8008,  -- Look at the stellar map? Yes. No.
        OH_I_I_M_SORRY_OF_COURSE_YOU                                           = 8009,  -- Oh, I-I'm sorry. Of course, you wouldn't be interested in stars... Goodbye!
        I_KNEW_YOU_D_BE_INTERESTED_THIS_MAP                                    = 8010,  -- I knew you'd be interested! This map was drawn by the famous Windurstian astronomer, Professor Lago-Charago!
        SEE_THAT_CONSTELLATION_TO_THE_SOUTH_THAT_S                             = 8011,  -- See that constellation to the south? That's Bastok's guardian, Titan! But not many people know that now. It's been a long time since we've celebrated Titan's Eve.
        THE_YELLOW_STAR_AT_ITS_CENTER_IS_DAEMDALUS                             = 8012,  -- The yellow star at its center is Daemdalus, or Titan's left foot. It used to be a lot brighter in the old days, and soldiers returning from battle followed it back to Bastok.
        I_M_GLAD_TO_HAVE_MET_SOMEONE_ELSE                                      = 8013,  -- I'm glad to have met someone else who likes looking at the stars. Maybe we can talk about them more sometime.
        YOU_ARE_IN_THE_METALWORKS_WOULD_YOU_LIKE                               = 8014,  -- You are in the Metalworks. Would you like to see a map of Bastok?
        LOOK_AT_MAP_OF_BASTOK_YES_NO                                           = 8015,  -- Look at map of Bastok? Yes. No.
        FACTORIES_THE_BLACKSMITHS_GUILD_AND_ADMINISTRATIVE_BUILDINGS_INCLUDING = 8016,  -- Factories, the Blacksmiths' Guild, and administrative buildings--including the President's Office--are all here in the Metalworks.
        THE_BLACKSMITHS_GUILD_IS_ON_THE_FIRST_FLOOR                            = 8017,  -- The Blacksmiths' Guild is on the first floor. Ride the elevator up to the second floor and go east past the water wheels to get to the President's Office.
        YOU_VE_BECOME_QUITE_AN_EXPERIENCED_ADVENTURER_I                        = 8018,  -- You've become quite an experienced adventurer, I hear. I feel I can trust you.
        I_NEED_YOU_TO_GO_ON_AN_ERRAND                                          = 8019,  -- I need you to go on an errand for me. Our supply of % is running low. Bring us two of them.
        THE_ZERUHN_MINES_HAVEN_T_BEEN_YIELDING_MUCH                            = 8020,  -- The Zeruhn Mines haven't been yielding much of it lately. You may have better luck in the Gusgen Mines.
        THANK_YOU_HERE_IS_YOUR_PAYMENT_IF_YOU                                  = 8021,  -- Thank you. Here is your payment. If you find any more, bring them here.
        HI_THIS_IS_WHERE_BLACKSMITHS_BUY_WHAT_THEY                             = 8022,  -- Hi. This is where blacksmiths buy what they need.
