        THERE_IS_AN_EMERGENCY_PROMPTLY_MAKE_YOUR_WAY                           = 8136,  -- There is an emergency. Promptly make your way to the President's Office. Ask Naji, and he will guide you.
        MASTER_OGGBI_THERE_WAS_NO_NEED_FOR_YOU                                 = 8137,  -- Master Oggbi! There was no need for you to come all the way here. We would have come to you.
        NO_WHEN_I_HEARD_OF_HIS_REVIVAL_MY                                      = 8138,  -- No, when I heard of his revival, my blood began to boil.
        WE_THINK_THAT_IT_MAY_BE_AN_OFFSPRING                                   = 8139,  -- We think that it may be an offspring of the new generation of Yagudo. We also feel that the Kindred's rise in power may also factor into his return.
        CURRENTLY_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_ARE_COMPRISED_SOLELY_OF               = 8140,  -- Currently, the Mythril Musketeers are comprised solely of warriors, samurai, and a missing dark knight. No competent monks exist.
        SAN_D_ORIA_IS_MORE_THAN_LIKELY_IN                                      = 8141,  -- San d'Oria is more than likely in the same predicament. The monastery is no longer able to produce the quality monks of old. And Windurst...those Tarutaru and their magic aren't good for anything.
        I_VE_MADE_ATTEMPTS_TO_CONTACT_NORG_BUT                                 = 8142,  -- I've made attempts to contact Norg, but no one seems willing to cooperate...
        IF_THEY_WON_T_EVEN_TAKE_UP_A                                           = 8143,  -- If they won't even take up a proposal from someone who did her training there, they definitely won't listen to me.
        NORG_NO_LONGER_HAS_ANY_INTEREST_IN_THE                                 = 8144,  -- Norg no longer has any interest in the way of the San d'Orian monks. Their attention has turned to the arts of the samurai and ninja.
        AND_DALZAKK_DALZAKK_IS_OFF_ON_ANOTHER_MISSION                          = 8145,  -- And Dalzakk... Dalzakk is off on another mission, so that leaves only...
        WHY_IF_IT_ISN_T_YOU_D_BE                                               = 8146,  -- Why, if it isn't %! You'd be perfect for the job!
        DO_YOU_THINK_YOU_D_BE_UP_TO                                            = 8147,  -- Do you think you'd be up to it?
        MASTER_OGGBI_I_THINK_OUR_ADVENTURER_HAS_YET                            = 8148,  -- Master Oggbi. I think our adventurer has yet to be informed on the details of this predicament.
        IT_ALL_BEGAN_THIRTY_YEARS_AGO_A_YAGUDO                                 = 8149,  -- It all began thirty years ago. A Yagudo with exponential power rose up in Vana'diel...
        MASTER_PLEASE_LET_ME_GO_WITH_YOU_I                                     = 8150,  -- Master! Please let me go with you! I'm more than ready!
        NO_NO_NO_YOU_MAY_HAVE_ENOUGH_POWER                                     = 8151,  -- No, no, no! You may have enough power to draw that Yagudo out of hiding, but you still lack the experience to defeat him.
        BUT_MASTER_THE_REASON_I_BECAME_YOUR_STUDENT                            = 8152,  -- But Master, the reason I became your student was so I could gain enough skill to defeat him... So I could avenge my brother's death...
        DO_YOU_THINK_I_DIDN_T_KNOW_THAT                                        = 8153,  -- Do you think I didn't know that? Your brother was a talented monk who met a tragic death. When you came to me, I put two and two together.
        HOWEVER_YOUR_VISION_IS_STILL_CLOUDED_CLOUDED_BY                        = 8154,  -- However, your vision is still clouded...clouded by the darkness of revenge.
        MASTER_OGGBI_YOU_HAVE_TRAINED_ME_WELL_AND                              = 8155,  -- Master Oggbi... You have trained me well, and I thank you. But if you believe that my vision is still clouded...
        THEN_I_MUST_SET_OUT_ON_MY_OWN                                          = 8156,  -- ...Then I must set out on my own to clear it!
        CORNELIA_2                                                             = 8157,  -- Cornelia...
        AND_SHE_SUCCEEDED_IN_BRINGING_DOWN_THAT_YAGUDO                         = 8158,  -- And she succeeded in bringing down that Yagudo. Whether that cleared her vision or not...
        WELL_HE_SHOWS_INTEREST_IN_MONKS_WHO_ARE                                = 8159,  -- Well, he shows interest in monks who are at his level of power, and only comes out when suitable opponents make their way into his lair.
        TAKE_AND_PLACE_IT_DEEP_WITHIN_THE_CASTLE                               = 8160,  -- Take % and place it deep within the castle. Your strength is certain to catch his eye and draw him out of hiding.
        IF_YOU_DEFEAT_HIM_HE_SHOULD_LEAVE_BRING                                = 8161,  -- If you defeat him, he should leave %. Bring that back to me and I will reward you for your efforts.
        THIS_IS_A_TASK_THAT_I_SHOULD_BE                                        = 8162,  -- This is a task that I should be taking on myself, but I just don't have the legs for it anymore...
        THIS_IS_SO_YOU_WERE_ABLE_TO_DEFEAT                                     = 8163,  -- This is... So you were able to defeat the Yagudo? I did not know such powerful monks still existed...
        LONG_AGO_MASTER_OGGBI_WORKED_HARD_TO_PROMOTE                           = 8164,  -- Long ago, Master Oggbi worked hard to promote the fusion of martial arts and San d'Orian combat techniques. Such a collaboration has obviously produced many outstanding fighters.
        EVEN_A_SAMURAI_SUCH_AS_MYSELF_IS_IN                                    = 8165,  -- Even a samurai such as myself is in awe of your extraordinary ability. Please accept this as payment for your service.
        ANOTHER_ITEM_HAD_BEEN_ARRANGED_FOR_YOU_BUT                             = 8166,  -- Another item had been arranged for you, but Master Oggbi asked to present this to you instead.
        I_SEE_YOU_HAVE_RETURNED_SAFELY_YOU_HAVE                                = 8167,  -- I see you have returned safely... You have matured well as a monk.
        THIS_IS_A_TOKEN_OF_MY_GRATITUDE_YOU                                    = 8168,  -- This is a token of my gratitude. You remind me much of Cornelia...
        YES_I_REMEMBER_SHE_CAME_TO_SEE_ME                                      = 8169,  -- Yes, I remember she came to see me in the Metalworks when she returned...
        CORNELIA_YOU_RE_FINALLY_BACK                                           = 8170,  -- Cornelia! You're finally back...
        MASTER_I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_CREATING_SO_MUCH_TROUBLE                        = 8171,  -- Master... I apologize for creating so much trouble.
        YOU_NEED_NOT_WORRY_OF_THAT_YOUR_VISION                                 = 8172,  -- You need not worry of that... Your vision... Is it still clouded as before?
        THAT_S_JUST_IT_I_THOUGHT_THAT_BY                                       = 8173,  -- That's just it... I thought that by avenging my brother's death, I would be free of the demons that haunted me...but in truth, I feel as though a part of me died when I defeated that Yagudo...
        I_SEE                                                                  = 8174,  -- I see...
        NOTHING_COMES_OF_REVENGE_IT_MERELY_RESULTS_IN                          = 8175,  -- Nothing comes of revenge. It merely results in us losing that which drives us.
        YOU                                                                    = 8176,  -- You...
        IT_IS_SAID_THAT_THOSE_WITH_NOTHING_TO                                  = 8177,  -- It is said that those with nothing to lose are often the strongest.
        MORE_THAN_LIKELY_YOU_FELT_THE_SAME_WAY                                 = 8178,  -- More than likely you felt the same way, Cornelia. But remember that if you have nothing to lose, you may have nothing at all...
        NOTHING_WORTH_PROTECTING_TRUE_STRENGTH_COMES_TO_THOSE                  = 8179,  -- ...nothing worth protecting. True strength comes to those who have something, or someone, to protect.
        AND_YOU_HAVE_SOMETHING_WORTH_PROTECTING                                = 8180,  -- And you...have something worth protecting?
        I_CARRY_WITH_ME_OVER_TWO_HUNDRED_YEARS                                 = 8181,  -- I carry with me over two hundred years of memories. At times they can be a burden, but it is my duty to protect them.
        TO_PROTECT_THE_SMILES_OF_THE_PEOPLE_IN                                 = 8182,  -- To protect the smiles of the people in those memories, I can handle the treatment I receive from those petty politicians in the President's Office.
        WILL_I_EVER_FIND_SOMETHING_SOMETHING_WORTH_PROTECTING                  = 8183,  -- Will I ever find something...something worth protecting?
        I_AM_CERTAIN_THAT_ONE_DAY_YOU_WILL                                     = 8184,  -- I am certain that one day you will.
        AND_THAT_WAS_THE_DAWN_OF_A_NEW                                         = 8185,  -- And that was the dawn of a new Musketeer in Cornelia.
        YOU_TOO_MUST_MAKE_A_PLEDGE_THAT_YOU                                    = 8186,  -- You, too, must make a pledge--that you will never use your ability to lose something. Make that pledge, and your power will never betray you.
        I_STILL_BELIEVE_TO_THIS_DAY_THAT_CORNELIA                              = 8187,  -- I still believe to this day that Cornelia made that pledge...
        WHAT_MY_GRANDMA_ASKED_YOU_TO_BRING_TO                                  = 8188,  -- What? My grandma asked you to bring % to me?
        I_CAN_T_BELIEVE_HER_MY_GRANDSON_THE                                    = 8189,  -- I can't believe her. My grandson the doorman. I get teased enough by Ayame, but to be ridiculed by my own flesh and blood! And this sword... What's the big deal, anyway?
        WHAT_S_WRONG_NAJI                                                      = 8190,  -- What's wrong, Naji?
        AH_SIR_IRON_EATER_MY_GRANDMOTHER                                       = 8191,  -- Ah, Sir Iron Eater. My grandmother...
        I_SEE_THIS_SWORD_BELONGED_TO_YOUR_FATHER                               = 8192,  -- I see. This sword belonged to your father, Lord Yasin. This may even be the sword that he used when...
        SIR_YOU_HAVE_MET_MY_FATHER_BEFORE                                      = 8193,  -- Sir? You have met my father before?
        ONCE_THIRTY_YEARS_AGO_BUT_I_WAS_STILL                                  = 8194,  -- Once, thirty years ago... But I was still a child.
        WELCOME_BACK_SIR_RAOGRIMM_DID_YOU_BEAT_UP                              = 8195,  -- Welcome back, Sir Raogrimm! Did you beat up some Orcs this time?
        PAGDAKO_MY_MISSION_THIS_TIME_WAS_A_SIMPLE                              = 8196,  -- Pagdako. My mission this time was a simple expedition. There was no beating up of any Orcs.
        YEAH_BUT_IT_MAKES_NO_DIFFERENCE_FOR_A                                  = 8197,  -- Yeah, but it makes no difference for a hired hand like me. I had me some fun, and found some good material for making a new sword to boot!
        WE_BUMPED_INTO_THIS_OTHER_PARTY_TOO_YEAH                               = 8198,  -- We bumped into this other party too... Yeah, some old monk traveling with a cute, feisty young girl.
        I_HAVE_NO_INTEREST_IN_THE_METHODS_YOU                                  = 8199,  -- I have no interest in the methods you use in finding good material, but I do know you are quite a fighter. It is a pity that you waste your talent on adventuring.
        OH_PLEASE_WHAT_ADVENTURES_AWAIT_ME_WITH_THE                            = 8200,  -- Oh, please. What adventures await me with the title of Musketeer? Guard duty? Heh, I'm no doorman!
        YOU_ARE_A_STRANGE_SORT_YASIN_THAT_MATERIAL                             = 8201,  -- You are a strange sort, Yasin. That material you brought back--I'll have one of my blacksmith companions make it into a sword for you. That will be your payment for your duties this time. Agreed?
        SOUNDS_GOOD_TO_ME_MUSKETEER                                            = 8202,  -- Sounds good to me, Musketeer.
        WHEN_I_GROW_UP_I_WANNA_BE_A                                            = 8203,  -- When I grow up, I wanna be a big, brave Musketeer, just like Sir Raogrimm!
        PAGDAKO_BEING_A_MUSKETEER_IS_NOT_NECESSARILY_ABOUT                     = 8204,  -- Pagdako, being a Musketeer is not necessarily about going out on missions and fighting monsters. At times, we must deal with enemies who are behind our own walls. If you can handle that burden as well, I believe you will make a fine Musketeer indeed.
        THERE_S_NO_DOUBT_ABOUT_IT_THAT_SWORD                                   = 8205,  -- There's no doubt about it. That sword is the one that Sir Raogrimm--the Mythril Musketeer and Galka Talekeeper himself--had made for your father.
        WOW_I_NEVER_KNEW_THAT_MY_FATHER_KNEW                                   = 8206,  -- Wow... I never knew that my father knew such important people. And Sir Iron Eater, I never knew your real name was...what did you say it was, Pacdaco?
        FEEL_FREE_TO_CALL_ME_WHICHEVER_IS_EASIEST                              = 8207,  -- ...... Feel free to call me whichever is easiest for you to pronounce. It makes no difference to me. A name is not important, only the man behind it.
        WELL_THANKS_FOR_BRINGING_THIS_TO_ME_I                                  = 8208,  -- Well, thanks for bringing this to me. I'll try to use it as my father did. Here, you can have this. It's been used quite a bit, but I'm sure you'll find a good home for it.
        YOU_RECEIVE_NOTHING_FROM_THE_MOON_RABBIT                               = 8209,  -- You receive nothing from the moon rabbit...
        THE_MOON_RABBIT_HAS_BROUGHT_ALONG_A_MONSTER                            = 8210,  -- The moon rabbit has brought along a monster!
        YOU_HAVE_TO_DO_SOMETHING_ABOUT_THOSE_CRAZY                             = 8211,  -- You have to do something about those crazy trees, kupo!
        YOU_RE_DONE_FIGHTING_TREES_KUPO                                        = 8212,  -- You're done fighting trees, kupo?
        GOOD_LUCK_I_WILL_BESTOW_UPON_YOU_YOUR                                  = 8220,  -- Good luck, [citizen/comrade]. I will bestow upon you your nation's Signet.
        I_CANNOT_HELP_YOU_YOU_SHOULD_GO_FIND                                   = 8221,  -- I cannot help you. You should go find a guard from your own country.
        I_CANNOT_ACCEPT_CRYSTALS_FROM_SOMEONE_WHOSE_RANK                       = 8222,  -- I cannot accept crystals from someone whose rank is still 1. I advise you to either keep them until your reach rank 2, or to use them in craftwork.
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_SAN_D_ORIA                                    = 8223,  -- Since we are allied with San d'Oria...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_BASTOK                                        = 8224,  -- Since we are allied with Bastok...
        SINCE_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_WINDURST                                      = 8225,  -- Since we are allied with Windurst...
        I_AM_SORRY_I_AM_TOO_BUSY_WITH                                          = 8226,  -- I am sorry. I am too busy with other matters to be speaking with you.
        AH_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_SUPPLIES_THESE_WILL                             = 8227,  -- Ah, you have brought us supplies. These will help us indeed. I thank you.
        HMM_THESE_SUPPLIES_YOU_HAVE_BROUGHT_US_ARE                             = 8228,  -- Hmm... These supplies you have brought us are too old to be of any use. We will dispose of them promptly. I do commend you for your effort. May you succeed next time.
        YOU_VE_EARNED_CONQUEST_POINTS                                          = 8229,  -- You've earned conquest points!
        YOU_VE_RECEIVED_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                               = 8230,  -- You've received your nation's Signet. You are now taking part in your nation's conquest campaign!
        I_AM_A_TEMPLE_KNIGHT_I_AM_ONE                                          = 8231,  -- I am , a Temple Knight. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing San d'Oria's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_AN_IRON_MUSKETEER_I_AM_ONE                                        = 8232,  -- I am , an Iron Musketeer. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Bastok's conquest campaign.
        I_AM_A_WAR_WARLOCK_I_AM_ONE                                            = 8233,  -- I am , a War Warlock. I am one of the guards charged with overseeing Windurst's conquest campaign.
        WHAT_IS_YOUR_BUSINESS_WOULD_YOU_CAST_SIGNET                            = 8234,  -- What is your business? Would you cast Signet on me? I want to spend my conquest points. [I want to join the Expeditionary Force./Teleport me to the E.F. area.] I want to quit the E.F./change my E.F. I want to go on a supplies quest. I have some questions... Nothing, sorry to bother you.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_NOTHING                                 = 8235,  -- What do you wish to know about? Nothing. Conquests. Conquest results. Donating crystals. Conquest points. The effects of controlling regions. Regions controlled by other nations. Regions under beastman control.
        ALL_THREE_NATIONS_ARE_STRIVING_DAILY_TO_PUT                            = 8236,  -- All three nations are striving daily to put more regions under their control. This is what we call conquests. You can take part in it and serve your country by defeating enemies while you have Signet cast on you.
        EACH_REGION_COMPRISES_SEVERAL_AREAS_AND_THE_NATION                     = 8237,  -- Each region comprises several areas, and the nation that rids those areas of the most monsters gains control of the region.
        NATIONS_RECEIVE_GOODS_AND_RESOURCES_FROM_REGIONS_UNDER                 = 8238,  -- Nations receive goods and resources from regions under their control.
        SO_THE_MORE_REGIONS_WE_CONTROL_THE_RICHER                              = 8239,  -- So, the more regions we control, the richer our nation becomes.
        BORDER_GUARDS_ARE_ALSO_PLACED_IN_OUTPOSTS_WITHIN                       = 8240,  -- Border guards are also placed in outposts within regions under our control. They are there to cast Signet on adventurers like yourself.
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_YOUR_NATION_S_SIGNET_YOU                                 = 8241,  -- Once you have your nation's Signet, you will be able to acquire crystals from enemies you defeat.
        NOT_ONLY_THAT_BUT_YOU_WILL_ALSO_RECEIVE                                = 8242,  -- Not only that, but you will also receive conquest points. You get more conquest points if you defeat enemies in regions that are not under your nation's control. These points can be used to purchase items from guards like myself.
        SO_YOU_SEE_CONQUESTS_BENEFIT_NATIONS_AND_ADVENTURERS                   = 8243,  -- So you see...conquests benefit nations and adventurers alike. We expect you to do your best to serve your country.
        YOU_CAN_SEE_THE_CURRENT_STATE_OF_CONQUESTS                             = 8244,  -- You can see the current state of conquests by selecting Region Info from the main menu. Conquest results in all regions are regularly recalculated, so you may want to check them from time to time.
        SHOPS_IN_OUR_CITY_WILL_BE_SELLING_DIFFERENT                            = 8245,  -- Shops in our city will be selling different items according to our conquest rank. The Troupe Valeriano will also visit the nation that finishes first and bring a little joy to its citizens.
        YOU_CAN_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO_YOUR_NATION_ONCE                            = 8246,  -- You can donate crystals to your nation once you achieve rank 2. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        WE_WOULD_LIKE_YOU_TO_DONATE_CRYSTALS_TO                                = 8247,  -- We would like you to donate crystals to your nation from now on. Just trade them to guards like myself, and we will ensure they are sent to the proper place.
        YOU_CAN_ACQUIRE_CRYSTALS_BY_DEFEATING_ENEMIES_WHILE                    = 8248,  -- You can acquire crystals by defeating enemies while you have your nation's Signet. Having Signet cast on you is also the only way of taking part in conquests.
        RANK_POINTS_WILL_BE_AWARDED_TO_YOU_FOR                                 = 8249,  -- Rank points will be awarded to you for each crystal you donate, and you may be offered new missions as your rank goes up.
        YOU_ALSO_RECEIVE_RANK_POINTS_FOR_COMPLETING_MISSIONS                   = 8250,  -- You also receive rank points for completing missions. Complete missions and take part in conquests to raise your rank and serve your country.
        YOU_ARE_AWARDED_CONQUEST_POINTS_WHEN_YOU_DEFEAT                        = 8251,  -- You are awarded conquest points when you defeat monsters while you are taking part in conquests. Select "Region Info" from the menu to check your current number of conquest points.
        YOU_CAN_PURCHASE_ITEMS_FROM_GUARDS_LIKE_MYSELF                         = 8252,  -- You can purchase items from guards like myself with your conquest points, but be warned that the number of points you spend will be subtracted from your current total.
        WHEN_CONQUEST_RESULTS_ARE_ANNOUNCED_YOU_WILL_BE                        = 8253,  -- When conquest results are announced, you will be told which country controls the region you are in at that time. Sometimes regions may become neutral, or beastmen may even gain control of regions.
        IF_WE_GAIN_CONTROL_OF_A_REGION_BORDER                                  = 8254,  -- If we gain control of a region, border guards will be placed at its outposts to help adventurers like you.
        MERCHANTS_WILL_ALSO_BE_PLACED_THERE_AND_GOODS                          = 8255,  -- Merchants will also be placed there, and goods from that region will find their way to the local shops here.
        GAINING_CONTROL_OF_REGIONS_IS_THE_BASIC_PRINCIPLE                      = 8256,  -- Gaining control of regions is the basic principle behind conquests. We need each of you to do your best, and bring our nation to the top of the ranks.
        OF_COURSE_SOMETIMES_WE_LOSE_REGIONS_TO_OTHER                           = 8257,  -- Of course, sometimes we lose regions to other nations...so we must try to take them back before the next conquest results are announced.
        AS_AN_INCENTIVE_WE_WILL_AWARD_YOU_WITH                                 = 8258,  -- As an incentive, we will award you with more conquest points for defeating monsters in those regions.
        BUT_IF_WE_ARE_ALLIED_WITH_ANOTHER_NATION                               = 8259,  -- But if we are allied with another nation, you will only be awarded the regular rate for defeating monsters in our allies' regions. On the other hand, we will award you with more points for fighting in the top-ranked nation's regions.
        OUR_PARAMOUNT_CONCERN_LIES_IN_THE_BEASTMEN_GAINING                     = 8260,  -- Our paramount concern lies in the beastmen gaining control of our regions. If too many of us are defeated in a region, the beastmen will gain control of it.
        IF_THIS_HAPPENS_NOT_ONLY_IS_IT_A                                       = 8261,  -- If this happens, not only is it a great blow to our pride, but you will be unable to acquire any crystals in that region.
        THE_BEASTMEN_ARE_A_MENACE_TO_ALL_NATIONS                               = 8262,  -- The beastmen are a menace to all nations. If they rise to power, we must all unite and drive those vile creatures from that region.
        WE_NEED_YOU_TO_BRING_SUPPLIES_TO_THE                                   = 8263,  -- We need you to bring supplies to the outpost border guards who are placed in regions under our control.
        THERE_IS_ONE_OUTPOST_IN_EACH_REGION_SELECT                             = 8264,  -- There is one outpost in each region. Select Region Info from the menu, and look for the areas with a small flag mark on the map. That is where they are.
        HERE_ARE_THE_SUPPLIES_JUST_GIVE_THEM_TO                                = 8265,  -- Here are the supplies. Just give them to the guard at the outpost and your mission will be complete. Now, choose which outpost you want to go to. We give different rewards for each region, so choose carefully.
        WHERE_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_TAKE_THE_SUPPLIES                                 = 8266,  -- Where do you wish to take the supplies? @ @ @ @ @ The Ronfaure Region.[/ (Done)] The Zulkheim Region.[/ (Done)] The Norvallen Region.[/ (Done)] The Gustaberg Region.[/ (Done)] The Derfland Region.[/ (Done)] The Sarutabaruta Region.[/ (Done)] The Kolshushu Region.[/ (Done)] The Aragoneu Region.[/ (Done)] The Fauregandi Region.[/ (Done)] The Valdeaunia Region.[/ (Done)] Qufim Island.[/ (Done)] The Li'Telor Region.[/ (Done)] The Kuzotz Region.[/ (Done)] The Vollbow Region.[/ (Done)] The Elshimo Lowlands Region.[/ (Done)] The Elshimo Uplands Region.[/ (Done)] Tu'Lia.[/ (Done)] @ The Tavnazian Archipelago.[/ (Done)] @ @ @ @ @ @ @ Cancel.
        WHICH_E_F_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_JOIN                                       = 8267,  -- Which E.F. would you like to join? . . . . . . The Zulkheim Region (Lv.20`). The Norvallen Region (Lv.25`). . The Derfland Region (Lv.25`). . The Kolshushu Region (Lv.20`). The Aragoneu Region (Lv.25`). The Fauregandi Region (Lv.35`). The Valdeaunia Region (Lv.40`). The Qufim Region (Lv.25`). The Li'Telor Region (Lv.35`). The Kuzotz Region (Lv.40`). The Vollbow Region (Lv.65`). The Elshimo Lowlands Region (Lv.35`). The Elshimo Uplands Region (Lv.45`). . . . . . . . . . . None.
        SO_BE_IT_YOU_HAVE_UNTIL_THE_NEXT                                       = 8268,  -- So be it. You have until the next conquest results announcement to complete this mission. Good luck.
        WE_WILL_DISPOSE_OF_THOSE_UNUSABLE_SUPPLIES                             = 8269,  -- We will dispose of those unusable supplies.
        YOU_CAN_ONLY_UNDERTAKE_ONE_SUPPLY_MISSION_PER                          = 8270,  -- You can only undertake one supply mission per day. Come back later.
        I_AM_SORRY_WE_SEEM_TO_HAVE_A                                           = 8271,  -- I am sorry. We seem to have a problem. Let me cancel it.
        YOU_DO_NOT_NEED_TO_DONATE_ANY_MORE                                     = 8272,  -- You do not need to donate any more crystals at your current rank. Speak to the guard at the gatehouse for further instructions.
        YOUR_RANK_POINTS_ARE_FULL_WE_VE_ADDED                                  = 8273,  -- Your rank points are full. We've added the excess to your conquest points. You do not need to donate any more crystals. Go to the gatehouse for further instructions.
        GOOD_WORK_CITIZEN_WE_VE_AWARDED_YOU_RANK                               = 8274,  -- Good work, citizen. We've awarded you rank points for the crystals you've donated.
        YOU_CURRENTLY_HAVE_CONQUEST_POINTS_WOULD_YOU_LIKE                      = 8275,  -- You currently have # conquest points. Would you like to use them to purchase items?
        WHICH_ITEM_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PURCHASE_COMMON                              = 8276,  -- Which item do you wish to purchase? Common items (all ranks). 1000-pt. items (rank 1 required).000-pt. items (rank 2 required). 4000-pt. items (rank 3 required). 8000-pt. items (rank 4 required). 16000-pt. items (rank 5 required).4000-pt. items (rank 6 required).2000-pt. items (rank 7 required). 40000-pt. items (rank 8 required). 48000-pt. items (rank 9 required). 56000-pt. items (rank 10 required). Cancel.
        WHICH_ITEM_DO_YOU_WISH_TO_PURCHASE_COMMON_2                            = 8277,  -- Which item do you wish to purchase? Common items (all ranks).000-pt. items (rank 1 required). 4000-pt. items (rank 2 required). 8000-pt. items (rank 3 required). 16000-pt. items (rank 4 required).4000-pt. items (rank 5 required).2000-pt. items (rank 6 required). 40000-pt. items (rank 7 required). 48000-pt. items (rank 8 required). 56000-pt. items (rank 9 required). . Cancel.
        CURRENTLY_THERE_ARE_NO_ITEMS_AVAILABLE_FOR_THAT                        = 8278,  -- Currently there are no items available for that rank.
        DUE_TO_ITS_SPECIAL_NATURE_YOU_CAN_ONLY                                 = 8279,  -- Due to its special nature, you can only purchase or recharge % once until the conquest results tally is performed. Also, you cannot purchase this item if a similar item is already in your possession.
        IT_IS_POSSIBLE_TO_FULLY_RECHARGE_BY_TRADING                            = 8280,  -- It is possible to fully recharge % by trading it to one of your nation's guards, including outpost guards. One charge requires 50 conquest points.
        IT_IS_POSSIBLE_TO_FULLY_RECHARGE_BY_TRADING_2                          = 8281,  -- It is possible to fully recharge % by trading it to one of your nation's guards, including outpost guards. One charge requires 100 conquest points.
