        PAUSE                                                                  = 8560,  -- PAUSE
        YOU_RE_A_DARK_KNIGHT_I_SEE_I                                           = 8562,  -- You're a dark knight, I see. I have a favor to ask that may be of some interest to you.
        THE_GALKA_METHODS_OF_DARKSTEEL_WORKING_ARE_RECENTLY                    = 8563,  -- The Galka methods of darksteel-working are recently being looked on in a different light. This, coupled with the recent rise in adventurers bringing in darksteel ore, has resulted in an increase in the production of darksteel goods.
        THIS_IS_WHY_I_NEED_AN_OLD_BOOK                                         = 8564,  -- This is why I need an old book called %.
        I_HEARD_THAT_IT_WAS_ONCE_KEPT_HERE                                     = 8565,  -- I heard that it was once kept here in the Metalworks, but I have no knowledge of its present location.
        THEY_SAY_THAT_IN_THE_OLDEN_DAYS_ALL                                    = 8566,  -- They say that in the olden days, all dark knight equipment was forged from darksteel. I would be willing to repay you handsomely if you could retrieve that book for me.
        WHAT_YOU_SAY_RAIBAHT_IS_SEARCHING_FOR_THE                              = 8567,  -- What? You say Raibaht is searching for the book %?
        I_SEE_HE_S_FINALLY_COME_TO_HIS                                         = 8568,  -- I see he's finally come to his senses. I've been trying to get him to ask Chief Cid to pour more money into the darksteel program.
        WELL_KNOWING_RAIBAHT_HE_PROBABLY_HAD_TO_THINK                          = 8569,  -- Well, knowing Raibaht, he probably had to think and re-think it, but he still hasn't made up his mind. Hopefully, seeing % will help to push him in the right direction.
        THE_PROBLEM_IS_WAS_DONATED_TO_A_LIBRARY                                = 8570,  -- The problem is, % was donated to a library somewhere before I was appointed to this position.
        AND_ON_TOP_OF_THAT_THERE_S_NO                                          = 8571,  -- And on top of that, there's no record of the donation anywhere. I guess I can't complain. That was back in the day when mythril was the material of choice, cermet was getting all the funding, and darksteel...well, darksteel was about as popular as rusty buckets...
        AND_WORTH_ABOUT_THE_SAME_TOO                                           = 8572,  -- ...and worth about the same, too.
        I_WILL_WRITE_A_LETTER_TO_THE_LIBRARY                                   = 8573,  -- I will write a letter to the library holding the document. You will need to take this letter and show it to the proprietor of the library.
        EXCELLENT_YOU_VE_RETRIEVED_OUR_COPY_OF_QUICKLY                         = 8574,  -- Excellent! You've retrieved our copy of %! Quickly, take it to Raibaht.
        YES_THIS_IS_THE_BOOK_I_WAS_IN                                          = 8575,  -- Yes, this is the book I was in search of. Please accept this for your troubles. It is a sample product forged by our head smith--and I assure you, it is of the highest quality.
        NOW_I_CAN_CONTINUE_MY_RESEARCH_ON_THE                                  = 8576,  -- Now I can continue my research on the forging of darksteel...and make a decision on whether or not to ask Chief Cid for more funding.
        YOU_WERE_GOING_TO_ASK_ME_WHAT_NOW                                      = 8577,  -- You were going to ask me what, now?
        I_AM_JUST_WORKING_ON_A_PERSONAL_PROJECT                                = 8578,  -- I am just working on a personal project.
        EVERY_TIME_YOU_SAY_THAT_IT_MEANS_YOU                                   = 8579,  -- Every time you say that, it means you're up to something.
        WHAT_S_THIS_AH_HA                                                      = 8580,  -- What's this? Ah-ha, %...
        ALLOW_ME_TO_CARRY_OUT_THIS_RESEARCH_CHIEF                              = 8581,  -- Allow me to carry out this research, Chief Cid. I am sure you are busy with your numerous projects.
        NOW_NOW_DON_T_YOU_WORRY_ABOUT_THAT                                     = 8582,  -- Now, now. Don't you worry about that. It's not what's in the book that interests me... It's the name of the person who wrote it.
        GERWITZ_I_M_POSITIVE_I_VE_HEARD_THAT                                   = 8583,  -- Gerwitz... I'm positive I've heard that name somewhere before...
        I_WILL_INVESTIGATE_THE_AUTHOR_FOR_YOU_AS                               = 8584,  -- I will investigate the author for you as well. If you spend too much time poking around, Chief, people will get the wrong idea...
        THAT_S_IT_I_REMEMBER_NOW                                               = 8585,  -- That's it! I remember now!
        GERWITZ_THE_GUY_WHO_WROTE_HE_WAS_THE                                   = 8586,  -- Gerwitz--the guy who wrote %! He was the one who forged Zeid's armor.
        A_STRANGE_GUY_THAT_ZEID_I_NEVER_THOUGHT                                = 8587,  -- A strange guy, that Zeid. I never thought he'd tell me where he had gotten that armor.
        WHAT_IS_THAT_YOU_SAY_YOU_HAVE_MET                                      = 8588,  -- What is that? You say you have met Zeid? A wee bit detached from the rest of the world, don't you think? Still, he fought alongside Volker and me during the Great War, and he was the one who defeated the Shadow Lord in the end.
        WELL_NOT_REALLY_BY_MY_SIDE_I_WAS                                       = 8589,  -- Well, not really by my side. I was mainly in the back, servicing the cannons...
        CHIEF_I_FORGOT_TO_GIVE_YOU_THIS_LETTER                                 = 8590,  -- Chief. I forgot to give you this letter from Zeid.
        WHAT_YOU_MEAN_THAT_BROODING_RECLUSE_ACTUALLY_SENT                      = 8591,  -- What!? You mean that brooding recluse actually sent me a letter...? Why didn't you give this to me sooner!?
        IT_ONLY_ARRIVED_EARLIER_TODAY                                          = 8592,  -- It only arrived earlier today.
        SO_WHAT_DOES_OLD_ZEID_HAVE_TO_SAY                                      = 8593,  -- So, what does old Zeid have to say? Hmm... Disturbing activity...a strange type of evil weapon...with a sword made by...Gerwitz!?
        WHAT_COULD_THIS_MEAN_DOES_ZEID_KNOW_SOMETHING                          = 8594,  -- What could this mean...? Does Zeid know something that we don't...?
        IF_YOU_MEET_UP_WITH_ZEID_ANY_TIME                                      = 8595,  -- If you meet up with Zeid any time soon, could you help him with his investigation? Any information you can get us will shed some light on his movements.
        OBTAINED_3                                                             = 8596,  -- Obtained: # .
        HEY_THAT_S_ONE_OF_THOSE_QUADAV_DOLLS                                   = 8597,  -- Hey, that's one of those Quadav dolls. I used to collect those for good luck.
        I_DON_T_THINK_THAT_S_SOMETHING_I                                       = 8598,  -- I don't think that's something I would be boasting about, Naji.
        S_SIR_LUCIUS                                                           = 8599,  -- S-Sir Lucius!
        SOME_THEORIZE_THAT_THE_PALBOROUGH_MINES_WERE_ONCE                      = 8600,  -- Some theorize that the Palborough Mines were once holy lands for the Quadav, and that Bastok forced the beastmen from their land.
        AND_THOSE_DOLLS_THAT_YOU_COLLECT_ARE_ACTUALLY                          = 8601,  -- And those dolls that you collect are actually idols representing their ancestral hero.
        OF_COURSE_THIS_HAS_NOTHING_TO_DO_WITH                                  = 8602,  -- Of course, this has nothing to do with your mission. Those pieces you have brought back are nothing more than proof of your success.
        BUT_REMEMBER_THIS_NAJI_THINGS_IN_THE_WORLD                             = 8603,  -- But remember this, Naji. Things in the world often look different depending on where you stand. Even though we are not obligated to search for knowledge, truth is only found by those who have the will...
        YOU_KNOW_SOMETIMES_I_JUST_DON_T_GET                                    = 8604,  -- You know, sometimes I just don't get what he's saying. He's usually like that after battling it out with the senators. Poor guy...
        GREAT_YOU_BROUGHT_ME                                                   = 8605,  -- Great! You brought me %!
        I_ASKED_YOU_TO_BRING_ME_THIS_BECAUSE                                   = 8606,  -- I asked you to bring me this because I'm thinking of using it in my next project. % can only be found in the Gusgen Mines, and with the mines being deserted for so many years...
        CHIEF_CID_DO_YOU_THINK_IT_WOULD_BE                                     = 8607,  -- Chief Cid. Do you think it would be possible to borrow that % after you have completed your project?
        OH_THIS_IS_A_SURPRISE_IT_S_NOT                                         = 8608,  -- Oh? This is a surprise. It's not every day that you ask me a favor.
        IT_IS_SAID_THAT_THE_GUSGEN_MINES_ARE                                   = 8609,  -- It is said that the Gusgen Mines are a haven for paranormal activity. Priests from the San d'Oria Cathedral have even performed certain rituals of consecration there. As far as magic research is concerned, it's certainly a significant location.
        I_HAVE_THE_FEELING_THAT_I_M_ABOUT                                      = 8610,  -- I have the feeling that I'm about to get a lecture on why the presidential aide shouldn't be dabbling in magic.
        DON_T_GET_ME_WRONG_LUCIUS_I_DON                                        = 8611,  -- Don't get me wrong, Lucius. I don't know squat about magic, but I've never questioned its power.
        I_KNOW_DARN_WELL_THAT_YOU_VE_SPENT                                     = 8612,  -- I know darn well that you've spent your career trying to get the people of Bastok to see the benefits of magic.
        YOU_MANAGED_TO_GET_SAN_D_ORIA_TO                                       = 8613,  -- You managed to get San d'Oria to cooperate with us in the creation of new magic spells by making good use of the results of my Crystal Line research. Those new spells have helped bring many mage adventurers to Bastok.
        SO_NEVER_DOUBT_YOUR_CAUSE_HERE_TAKE_THIS                               = 8614,  -- So never doubt your cause. Here, take this %. My research can wait.
        I_I_AM_AT_A_LOSS_FOR_WORDS                                             = 8615,  -- I...I am at a loss for words...
        AND_LET_ME_TELL_YOU_ONE_MORE_THING                                     = 8616,  -- And let me tell you one more thing. You don't go and overwork yourself, hear? You're one of the few people in this city who Karst needs. You go down, and he goes down.
        THERE_HAS_BEEN_SOME_COMMOTION_IN_THE_MINES                             = 8617,  -- There has been some commotion in the Mines District near Ore Street. People are saying that a new Talekeeper has appeared.
        IT_SOUNDS_FISHY_TO_ME_BUT_WITH_THE                                     = 8618,  -- It sounds fishy to me, but with the disappearance of their elder, Werei, anything could be possible. And the last thing we want is an uprising by the Galka.
        GO_TO_ORE_STREET_AND_TALK_TO_MEDICINE                                  = 8619,  -- Go to Ore Street and talk to Medicine Eagle. He says he was there when the commotion started.
        I_ASSUME_AN_ADVENTURER_OF_YOUR_CALIBER_HAS                             = 8620,  -- I assume an adventurer of your caliber has heard of Norg.
        WELL_THE_PLACE_IS_A_HAVEN_FOR_PIRATES                                  = 8621,  -- Well, the place is a haven for pirates. They even have ties with the Tenshodo. In any case, it's an area that cannot be looked upon lightly.
        THAT_IS_WHY_WE_WANT_YOU_TO_TRAVEL                                      = 8622,  -- That is why we want you to travel there as an emissary. Report to Sir Naji in the President's Office for details.
        CURRENTLY_CHIEF_ENGINEER_CID_IS_CONDUCTING_RESEARCH_ON                 = 8623,  -- Currently, Chief Engineer Cid is conducting research on the architecture in Ro'Maeve near the Sanctuary of Zi'Tah. Your next mission is to travel there and assist him.
        REPORT_TO_THE_CHIEF_ENGINEER_IN_THE_METALWORKS                         = 8624,  -- Report to the Chief Engineer in the Metalworks for further details.
        WE_ARE_SEARCHING_FOR_AN_ADVENTURER_HOLDING_VITAL                       = 8625,  -- We are searching for an adventurer holding vital information dealing with a certain national investigation.
        THE_PRESIDENT_HIMSELF_HAS_EXPRESSED_GREAT_INTEREST_IN                  = 8626,  -- The president himself has expressed great interest in this case. Proceed to the President's Office for the details of this mission.
        YOU_VE_BEEN_ORDERED_BY_THE_PRESIDENT_TO                                = 8627,  -- You've been ordered by the president to deliver that %. When you have completed that task, you can return here for your next mission.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_BASTOK_IS_REALLY_GOING_TO                                = 8628,  -- It looks like Bastok is really going to begin an investigation of the Galka homeland of Altepa.
        YOUR_ROLE_IN_THIS_INVESTIGATION_WILL_HAVE_YOU                          = 8629,  -- Your role in this investigation will have you traveling to the Quicksand Caves. Get the details of this mission from Iron Eater in the President's Office.
        AS_A_CONTINUATION_OF_BASTOK_S_INVESTIGATION_OF                         = 8630,  -- As a continuation of Bastok's investigation of Altepa, this time you will be traveling to Zepwell Island.
        YOU_WILL_BE_CARRYING_OUT_YOUR_PART_OF                                  = 8631,  -- You will be carrying out your part of the investigation in the Kuftal Tunnel, which connects Cape Teriggan to Zepwell Island. Report to Drake Fang in the Zeruhn Mines for details.
        SENATOR_ALOIS_HAS_ASKED_FOR_YOUR_ASSISTANCE                            = 8632,  -- Senator Alois has asked for your assistance.
        IT_IS_SOMETHING_ABOUT_AN_EXPEDITION_TO_VOLLBOW                         = 8633,  -- It is something about an expedition to Vollbow...
        I_JUST_HOPE_HE_S_NOT_ASKING_YOU                                        = 8634,  -- I just hope he's not asking you to go get lizard eggs again... Wait, you didn't hear me say that.
        RECENTLY_AN_ADVENTURER_WHO_WAS_SENT_TO_INVESTIGATE                     = 8635,  -- Recently, an adventurer who was sent to investigate the Northlands has been attacked.
        ACCORDING_TO_HER_REPORT_THE_ATTACKER_RESEMBLED_THE                     = 8636,  -- According to her report, the attacker resembled the dark knight Zeid.
        THE_STRANGE_THING_IS_THAT_THE_ATTACKER_PASSED                          = 8637,  -- The strange thing is that the attacker passed a letter to the adventurer before letting her go. Now, this letter's content is causing quite a commotion in the President's Office.
        YOU_HAVE_BEEN_ASKED_TO_REPORT_DIRECTLY_TO                              = 8638,  -- You have been asked to report directly to President Karst for further details.
        AH_IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_RE_READY_FOR                                      = 8639,  -- Ah, %. It looks like you're ready for your next mission. I've heard that you're traveling to Norg this time.
        WHAT_I_M_SUPPOSED_TO_BE_GIVING_YOU                                     = 8640,  -- What? I'm supposed to be giving you the details? That's funny. I don't remember being assigned to this mission...
        IT_LOOKS_AS_IF_THE_GUARD_MIXED_THE                                     = 8641,  -- It looks as if the guard mixed the two of us up--as if that could happen. I'm the one who will be relaying the adventurer's orders.
        AS_IF_THAT_COULD_HAPPEN                                                = 8642,  -- As if that could happen!?
        YOUR_MISSION_TO_NORG_IS_THAT_OF_A                                      = 8643,  -- Your mission to Norg is that of a trade emissary.
        NORG_IS_CONSTANTLY_ATTEMPTING_TO_STRENGTHEN_ITS_TIES                   = 8644,  -- Norg is constantly attempting to strengthen its ties with adventurers. They often rely on them to do certain jobs involving trade.
        COMPARED_TO_WINDURST_AND_SAN_D_ORIA_BASTOK                             = 8645,  -- Compared to Windurst and San d'Oria, Bastok's relations with Norg run much deeper. That is why, for the sake of our republic's commerce, we are sending adventurers to such a remote location.
        I_WAS_TO_ACCOMPANY_YOU_ON_THIS_MISSION                                 = 8646,  -- I was to accompany you on this mission, but first I must complete another small task.
        TRAVEL_TO_NORG_AND_MEET_WITH_THEIR_LEADER                              = 8647,  -- Travel to Norg and meet with their leader, Gilgamesh. He will give you further information on what you are to do. I will rendezvous with you in Norg when I have finished my current assignment.
        AND_THAT_S_THE_GIST_OF_IT_WAIT                                         = 8648,  -- And that's the gist of it... Wait. Before you go, could you come over here for a second?
        THE_REASON_I_CALLED_YOU_OVER_HERE_IS                                   = 8649,  -- The reason I called you over here is that I want you to try to finish this mission ASAP...preferably, before Ayame arrives.
        I_KNOW_THIS_MUST_SOUND_STRANGE_BUT_YOU                                 = 8650,  -- I know this must sound strange, but you've got to help me out here. Recently Ayame has been acting...well, strange. It's like she's missing that, that something.
        THE_OTHER_DAY_SHE_WAS_DEFEATED_BY_AN                                   = 8651,  -- The other day, she was defeated by an enemy that, well, even you could take out.
        AND_NOW_SHE_S_USING_THAT_AS_AN                                         = 8652,  -- And now she's using that as an excuse to restart her samurai training.
        YOU_CAN_PROBABLY_TELL_BY_LOOKING_AT_ME                                 = 8653,  -- You can probably tell by looking at me, but we Mythril Musketeers don't spend much time out there on the front lines.
        THAT_MAKES_IT_HARD_FOR_US_TO_KEEP                                      = 8654,  -- That makes it hard for us to keep our battle skills brushed up. I think that's what's bothering Ayame. She wants to get back what she thinks she has lost.
        AND_NOW_SHE_WANTS_TO_TRAVEL_TO_NORG                                    = 8655,  -- And now she wants to travel to Norg. That will just make things worse!
        AS_MUCH_AS_I_WANT_TO_BE_NUMBER                                         = 8656,  -- As much as I want to be number four, I don't want it because she leaves. That's why she's got to remain a Musketeer.
        YOU_KNOW_WHAT_YOU_VE_GOT_TO_DO                                         = 8657,  -- You know what you've got to do! And keep quiet about this to Ayame...
        YOU_RE_FINALLY_BACK_FROM_NORG_SO_DID                                   = 8658,  -- You're finally back from Norg. So, did you see Ayame?
        YOU_MEAN_SHE_SAID_ALL_OF_THAT                                          = 8659,  -- You mean, she said all of that?
        I_GUESS_SHE_WENT_TO_NORG_TO_RECONFIRM                                  = 8660,  -- I guess she went to Norg to reconfirm what she already knew deep down in her heart.
        HEY_DON_T_YOU_GO_OFF_TELLING_HER                                       = 8661,  -- Hey, don't you go off telling her that I was worried about her, now!
        IT_S_JUST_THAT_WELL_AYAME_GETS_ALL                                     = 8662,  -- It's just that, well, Ayame gets all the good missions while I get zilch. I wish I got to go to Norg...
        I_DON_T_THINK_NORG_NEEDS_ANY_MORE                                      = 8663,  -- I don't think Norg needs any more doorboys.
        YEAH_YOU_RE_PROBABLY_RIGHT                                             = 8664,  -- Yeah, you're probably right...
        WAIT_A_MINUTE_WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_DOORBOY                                 = 8665,  -- Wait a minute! What do you mean, doorboy!?
        YOU_MOVE_ONE_INCH_FROM_YOUR_POST_AND                                   = 8666,  -- You move one inch from your post and I'll have you on latrine duty!
        YES_MA_AM_ALL_CLEAR_ON_THE_NORTHERN                                    = 8667,  -- Yes, ma'am. All clear on the northern front...
        AH_IT_S_NICE_TO_SEE_YOU_AGAIN                                          = 8668,  -- Ah, it's nice to see you again. But enough with the greetings; let me tell you about your next mission.
        YOU_VE_HEARD_OF_THE_ANCIENT_CIVILIZATION_OF                            = 8669,  -- You've heard of the ancient civilization of the Zilart, haven't you? Well, there are archeological remains of this civilization scattered about Vana'diel.
        THE_ZILART_USED_A_MATERIAL_CALLED_CERMET_TO                            = 8670,  -- The Zilart used a material called cermet to construct many of these structures. This cermet is more advanced than anything found in Bastok.
        RESEARCHING_AND_REPRODUCING_THIS_MATERIAL_WOULD_DO_WONDERS             = 8671,  -- Researching and reproducing this material would do wonders for Bastok's industry. Ancient cermet technology is the building block of the future, so to speak.
        DEEP_WITHIN_THE_SANCTUARY_OF_ZI_TAH_YOU                                = 8672,  -- Deep within the Sanctuary of Zi'Tah you will find the entrance to Ro'Maeve. I want you to bring me some % from there.
        I_LL_BE_WAITING_FOR_YOU_HERE                                           = 8673,  -- I'll be waiting for you here.
        HA_HA_YOU_GOT_YOUR_HANDS_ON_NOW                                        = 8674,  -- Ha ha! You got your hands on %! Now I can continue my cermet research.
        CHIEF_CID                                                              = 8675,  -- Chief Cid...
        DON_T_YOU_GO_GETTING_YOUR_FEATHERS_RUFFLED                             = 8676,  -- Don't you go getting your feathers ruffled, Raibaht. I'm not going to be making any cuts in darksteel research.
        CHIEF_WE_HAVE_A_VISITOR                                                = 8677,  -- Chief, we have a visitor.
        THANK_YOU                                                              = 8678,  -- Thank you.
        WHAT_S_WRONG_CORNELIA_DID_YOU_HAVE_A                                   = 8679,  -- What's wrong, Cornelia? Did you have a fight with your father again?
        IT_S_NOT_ANYTHING_LIKE_THAT_BUT_IT                                     = 8680,  -- It's not anything like that...but it does have to do with my father.
        JUST_A_FEW_MINUTES_AGO_I_MET_WITH                                      = 8681,  -- Just a few minutes ago, I met with this young Galka.
        OH_THERE_YOU_ARE_CORNELIA                                              = 8682,  -- Oh! There you are, Cornelia!
        GUMBAH_WHY_DID_YOU_FOLLOW_ME                                           = 8683,  -- Gumbah! Why did you follow me?
        I_HAD_SOMETHING_I_WANTED_TO_ASK_YOU                                    = 8684,  -- I had something I wanted to ask you, and I was worried about what I was going to do if I couldn't find you.
        HEY_WAIT_YOU_AREN_T_GOING_TO_SEND                                      = 8685,  -- Hey, wait. You aren't going to send me on one of your weird quests, are you? I can't trust you after the last time.
        I_NEVER_MADE_YOU_DO_ANYTHING_THAT_WEIRD                                = 8686,  -- I never made you do anything that weird! Anyway, this time is different. I want you to search for Werei for me.
        YOU_MEAN_THE_SAME_WEREI_THAT_YOU_LIVED                                 = 8687,  -- You mean the same Werei that you lived with a while back? The same Werei that disappeared...
        HE_HASN_T_DISAPPEARED_HE_S_SET_OUT                                     = 8688,  -- He hasn't disappeared... He's set out on his journey of rebirth. I don't expect to ever see him in the form of Werei again.
        BUT_LEAVING_WITHOUT_SAYING_ANYTHING_IT_JUST_DOESN                      = 8689,  -- But, leaving without saying anything... It just doesn't make any sense. There must be some reason.
        AND_SO_I_THOUGHT_THAT_IF_I_ASKED                                       = 8690,  -- And so I thought that if I asked you, you might be able to do something. The situation in the Mines District is not getting any better, and any information would help.
        BUT_I_DON_T_KNOW_IF_I_COULD                                            = 8691,  -- But, I don't know if I could be of any help...
        WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_YOUR_DAD_S_THE                                        = 8692,  -- What do you mean? Your dad's the president. Couldn't you just ask him to help you out?
        HOW_DID_YOU_KNOW_THAT                                                  = 8693,  -- How did you know that...!?
        YOU_THINK_I_DIDN_T_ALREADY_KNOW_EVERYBODY                              = 8694,  -- You think I didn't already know? Everybody knows. Are you still in the dark?
        WELL_EVEN_IF_I_AM_THE_PRESIDENT_S                                      = 8695,  -- Well...even if I am the president's daughter, I can't use my position like that. It wouldn't be right.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_YOU_RE_ALWAYS_SAYING                                  = 8696,  -- What do you mean? You're always saying that you want to help the Galka!
        YOU_WEREN_T_LYING_WERE_YOU_OR_WAS                                      = 8697,  -- You weren't lying, were you? Or was that just your way of showing pity for us poor Galka?
        GUMBAH_HOW_COULD_YOU_SAY_THAT_OF_COURSE                                = 8698,  -- Gumbah! How could you say that? Of course I want to help you, it's just that...
        YOU_RE_JUST_SAYING_THAT_TO_MAKE_YOUR                                   = 8699,  -- You're just saying that to make your ego feel better. Whether you like it or not, you are in a position of power.
        WHY_DON_T_YOU_USE_THAT_POWER_STOP                                      = 8700,  -- Why don't you use that power? Stop trying to run from...it...
        WHAT_IF_YOU_HAVE_SOMETHING_TO_SAY_TO                                   = 8701,  -- What!? If you have something to say to me, say it!
        I_M_SORRY_CORNELIA_I_DIDN_T_MEAN                                       = 8702,  -- I'm sorry, Cornelia. I didn't mean that... Forget what I said. I'll try searching for Werei on my own.
        THAT_GUMBAH_I_CAN_T_BELIEVE_HIM_SOMETIMES                              = 8703,  -- That Gumbah! I can't believe him sometimes!
        SO_DID_YOU_TALK_TO_YOUR_FATHER                                         = 8704,  -- So, did you talk to your father?
        NO_I_COULDN_T_ASK_HIM_FOR_HELP                                         = 8705,  -- No... I couldn't ask him for help.
        CORNELIA_I_M_JUST_A_SIMPLE_ENGINEER_I                                  = 8706,  -- Cornelia. I'm just a simple engineer. I don't know what the best choice is here.
        BUT_I_DO_KNOW_ONE_THING                                                = 8707,  -- But I do know one thing...
        BACK_IN_THE_DAYS_WHEN_BASTOK_WAS_FILLED                                = 8708,  -- Back in the days when Bastok was filled with old wooden houses, there was a big fire that wiped out most of the homes.
        HOWEVER_AT_THAT_TIME_BASTOK_WAS_A_POOR                                 = 8709,  -- However, at that time Bastok was a poor country, and very few funds could be used for the rebuilding of the houses.
        TWO_PROPOSITIONS_WERE_OFFERED_TO_THE_GOVERNMENT_ONE                    = 8710,  -- Two propositions were offered to the government. One was to collect donations.
        THE_OTHER_WAS_TO_GIVE_PRIORITY_TO_THE                                  = 8711,  -- The other was to give priority to the merchants of that area in exchange for contributions to the rebuilding. That was the plan proposed by your young father.
        WHICH_DO_YOU_THINK_IS_RIGHT_CORNELIA                                   = 8712,  -- Which do you think is right, Cornelia?
        ASKING_FOR_THE_DONATIONS_OF_PEOPLE                                     = 8713,  -- Asking...for the donations of people?
        I_GUESS_THAT_IS_ONE_WAY_OF_SOLVING                                     = 8714,  -- I guess that is one way of solving the problem. That's what the president at that time chose, and it helped get him votes.
        HOWEVER_SIX_MONTHS_WENT_BY_AND_THE_REBUILDING                          = 8715,  -- However, six months went by, and the rebuilding of the district was not even close to being finished. There were still people living out on the streets with no place to go.
        YOUR_FATHER_S_PLAN_WAS_FINALLY_PUT_INTO                                = 8716,  -- Your father's plan was finally put into effect, and slowly but surely, the district began to take shape once again.
        MAYBE_IT_S_JUST_THE_ENGINEER_IN_ME                                     = 8717,  -- Maybe it's just the engineer in me talking, but I think that when you're too busy choosing the parts, you sometimes lose sight of what you're really trying to make.
        DON_T_YOU_GO_AND_FORGET_WHAT_YOU                                       = 8718,  -- Don't you go and forget what you're trying to make now, Cornelia. You have to decide what you're going to do.
        OH_I_M_SORRY_YOU_HAD_TO_HEAR                                           = 8719,  -- Oh, %. I'm sorry you had to hear all that. You can go now. I'll make the report.
        THIS_YOU_BROUGHT_ME_THIS_WILL_HELP_ME                                  = 8720,  -- This % you brought me... This will help me get closer to what I'm really trying to make.
        THANK_YOU_FOR_COMING_CURRENTLY_WE_ARE_INVESTIGATING                    = 8721,  -- Thank you for coming, %. Currently, we are investigating the whereabouts of a certain Galka named Werei. You have heard of him, have you not?
        IT_SOUNDS_LIKE_ANOTHER_AGING_GALKA_HAS_JUST                            = 8722,  -- It sounds like another aging Galka has just set off on his journey of rebirth, but the residents of the Mining District are not taking this very well.
        THERE_IS_SO_MUCH_BIGOTRY_WHEN_IT_COMES                                 = 8723,  -- There is so much bigotry when it comes to these racial problems, it is hard to act on anything.
        HOWEVER_THERE_IS_ONE_THING_THAT_INTERESTS_ME                           = 8724,  -- However, there is one thing that interests me. There is a rumor that a certain adventurer has received a letter from this Werei.
        I_WOULD_LIKE_YOU_TO_FIND_THIS_ADVENTURER                               = 8725,  -- I would like you to find this adventurer and find out what he knows. However...
        COME_FOLLOW_ME                                                         = 8726,  -- Come, follow me.
        MILADY_AN_ADVENTURER_WOULD_LIKE_TO_SPEAK_WITH                          = 8727,  -- Milady. An adventurer would like to speak with you.
        DOES_THIS_MEAN_MY_FATHER_HAS_FINALLY_AGREED                            = 8728,  -- Does this mean my father has finally agreed to start an investigation!?
        FATHER_WHAT_IS_THE_MEANING_OF_THIS                                     = 8729,  -- Father! What is the meaning of this!?
        DON_T_GET_ME_WRONG_CORNELIA_IF_YOU                                     = 8730,  -- Don't get me wrong, Cornelia. If you want to lock yourself up in this room, I won't stop you.
        I_HAVE_RECEIVED_A_REPORT_FROM_IRON_EATER                               = 8731,  -- I have received a report from Iron Eater stating that finding the whereabouts of Werei may help calm down some of the Galka in the Mines District.
        I_AM_ONLY_HERE_TO_GATHER_INFORMATION_ON                                = 8732,  -- I am only here to gather information on the subject from those who may know something--namely you. I have no time for your petty games.
        BUT_WHEN_I_TRIED_TALKING_TO_YOU_BEFORE                                 = 8733,  -- But, when I tried talking to you before, you wouldn't...
        DO_YOU_HAVE_ANY_INFORMATION_FOR_ME_IF                                  = 8734,  -- Do you have any information for me? If not, I will assign this adventurer to another mission, and that will be the end of things.
        WAIT_I_DID_HEAR_SOMETHING_AT_THE_STEAMING                              = 8735,  -- Wait... I did hear something at the Steaming Sheep Restaurant. An adventurer named Hani...
        THIS_ADVENTURER_SAID_HE_MET_WEREI_WHILE_TRAVELING                      = 8736,  -- This adventurer said he met Werei while traveling through the Korroloka Tunnel, and received a letter from him.
        HOWEVER_SINCE_THEN_NO_ONE_HAS_SEEN_HIM                                 = 8737,  -- However, since then, no one has seen him.
        THE_PROPRIETOR_OF_THE_STEAMING_SHEEP_HILDA_MAY                         = 8738,  -- The proprietor of the Steaming Sheep, Hilda, may know more...
        UNDERSTOOD_WILL_TAKE_THE_INVESTIGATION_FROM_HERE                       = 8739,  -- Understood. % will take the investigation from here.
        WAIT_FATHER                                                            = 8740,  -- Wait, Father.
        AM_AM_I_FOOLISH_TO_THINK_I_CAN                                         = 8741,  -- Am...am I foolish to think I can make a difference, or am I just a hypocrite?
        CORNELIA_3                                                             = 8742,  -- Cornelia...
        I_ONCE_HEARD_A_FAR_EASTERN_LEGEND_THAT                                 = 8743,  -- I once heard a Far Eastern legend that stated hypocrisy is born from the acts of good that one performs.
        WHEREAS_THE_WORD_USED_TO_SYMBOLIZE_A_SIMPLE                            = 8744,  -- Whereas the word used to symbolize a simple act of human nature, over the years, the meaning of the word became warped to the negative tone that it holds today.
        WHENEVER_ANYONE_TRIES_TO_DO_ANYTHING_THERE_WILL                        = 8745,  -- Whenever anyone tries to do anything, there will always be someone there to judge them. I have experienced that my whole life, but it has never stopped me from pursuing my goals.
        I_WON_T_LET_ANYONE_STAND_IN_MY                                         = 8746,  -- I won't let anyone stand in my way.
        YOU_VE_GOT_A_GOOD_TEN_YEARS_BEFORE                                     = 8747,  -- You've got a good ten years before you can start complaining about what is right and what is wrong. Don't forget that.
        FATHER_3                                                               = 8748,  -- Father...
        YOU_HAVE_YOUR_ORDERS_SPEAK_WITH_HILDA_AT                               = 8749,  -- %. You have your orders. Speak with Hilda at the Steaming Sheep Restaurant and find out more on this Hani character.
        LADY_CORNELIA_HAS_LOCKED_HERSELF_IN_HER_ROOM                           = 8750,  -- Lady Cornelia has locked herself in her room and will not come out...
        WHAT_IS_THIS_YOU_SAY_THE_HANI_IN                                       = 8751,  -- What is this you say? The Hani in question got himself caught by the Quadav? By the sounds of it, you adventurers have quite a carefree lifestyle.
        WELL_NO_MATTER_WE_CAN_NOW_BE_CERTAIN                                   = 8752,  -- Well, no matter. We can now be certain that Werei set out on his journey of his own free will. Let me reward you for your service and raise your rank.
        THE_LETTER_YOU_CARRY_DELIVER_IT_TO_THE                                 = 8753,  -- The letter you carry--deliver it to the proper recipient. I am not going to let this problem escalate by meddling with it. Let the Galka see the truth with their own eyes.
        I_SEE_THAT_YOU_ALREADY_DELIVERED_THE_LETTER                            = 8754,  -- I see that you already delivered the letter to its proper recipient. I am not going to let this problem escalate by meddling with it. Let the Galka see the truth with their own eyes.
        WE_VE_BEEN_EXPECTING_YOU_CAPTAIN_VOLKER_IS                             = 8755,  -- We've been expecting you. Captain Volker is awaiting your arrival in the Conference Room.
        AH_FOR_YOUR_NEXT_MISSION_I_WOULD_LIKE                                  = 8756,  -- Ah, %. For your next mission, I would like you to travel to the Altepa Desert to investigate the Quicksand Caves. These caves are an important location amongst the ruins of the Galkan civilization.
        WHY_YOU_ASK_ARE_WE_STARTING_AN_INVESTIGATION                           = 8757,  -- Why, you ask, are we starting an investigation into the Galkan ruins?
        IT_ALL_STARTED_WITH_A_LETTER_ADDRESSED_TO                              = 8758,  -- It all started with a letter addressed to Iron Eater.
        THE_TIME_HAS_COME_TO_UNLOCK_THE_PAST                                   = 8759,  -- The time has come to unlock the past and step forth into the future. I await the adventurer near the statue of the Talekeeper in the Quicksand Caves.
        THERE_IS_NO_NAME_ON_THE_LETTER_BUT                                     = 8760,  -- There is no name on the letter, but I know who wrote it... Zeid.
        IF_I_COULD_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO_GO                                          = 8761,  -- If I could, I would like to go myself. However, if I did, Zeid would most certainly not show up.
        YOU_MET_WITH_ZEID_WHEN_YOU_DEFEATED_THE                                = 8762,  -- You met with Zeid when you defeated the Shadow Lord. If he would talk with anyone, it would be you.
        YOUR_MISSION_IS_TO_SEEK_OUT_THIS_STATUE                                = 8763,  -- Your mission is to seek out this statue of the Talekeeper and find out what Zeid meant about unlocking the past.
        THE_QUICKSAND_CAVES_ARE_SHROUDED_IN_MYSTERY_THERE                      = 8764,  -- The Quicksand Caves are shrouded in mystery. There is not much we know of the area. You may face many hardships during your investigation, but we are counting on your success.
        I_WELCOME_YOU_BACK_FROM_YOUR_JOURNEY_WHAT                              = 8765,  -- I welcome you back from your journey. What did you find in the Quicksand Caves?
        I_SEE_THE_HISTORY_OF_THE_GALKA                                         = 8766,  -- I see... The history of the Galka...
        ZEID_MUST_FEEL_THE_SAME_AS_I_DO                                        = 8767,  -- Zeid must feel the same as I do--that this is a turning point in our history.
        HOWEVER_HIS_MENTION_OF_THE_TALEKEEPER_DOES_HE                          = 8768,  -- However, his mention of the Talekeeper... Does he really believe that a new one is among us?
