        MAY_FORTUNE_SMILE_UPON_YOUR_FUTURE_ENDEAVORS                           = 9172,  -- May fortune smile upon your future endeavors, %.
        GOOD_DAY_SIR_MA_AM_I_AM_WITH                                           = 9173,  -- Good day, sir/ma'am]. I am with the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network (AMAN) and am now taking applications for new mentors.
        WHAT_IS_A_MENTOR_YOU_ASK_WELL_IN                                       = 9174,  -- What is a mentor, you ask? Well, in short, a mentor is an experienced adventurer who is willing to offer some of their time to help out their less traveled companions.
        IF_THIS_SOUNDS_LIKE_THE_JOB_FOR_YOU                                    = 9175,  -- If this sounds like the job for you, then feel free to sign up today.
        TO_BECOME_A_MENTOR_YOU_MUST_HAVE_COMPLETED                             = 9176,  -- To become a mentor, you must have completed the Records of Eminence objective %.
        ACCEPTING_REQUIRES_THAT_YOU_HAVE_OVER_180_HOURS                        = 9177,  -- Accepting % requires that you have over 180 hours of play time...
        AND_HAVE_COMPLETED_THE_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE_OBJECTIVE                   = 9178,  -- ...and have completed the Records of Eminence objective %.
        PLEASE_NOTE_THAT_REGISTERING_AND_SERVING_AS_A                          = 9179,  -- Please note that registering and serving as a mentor, as well as utilizing the services of the Mentor Program, are to be done at the player's own discretion.
        SQUARE_ENIX_WILL_NOT_BE_HELD_RESPONSIBLE_FOR                           = 9180,  -- SQUARE ENIX will not be held responsible for the actions and/or comments of any mentors. No benefits of any kind will be provided to those who choose to participate in the Mentor Program.
        WHEN_YOU_AGREE_TO_PARTICIPATE_IN_THE_MENTOR                            = 9181,  -- When you agree to participate in the Mentor Program, you are acknowledging that you have read and understood the above terms.
        I_AM_SORRY_BUT_YOU_DO_NOT_MEET                                         = 9182,  -- I am sorry, but you do not meet the requirements necessary to accept the Records of Eminence objective %.
        PLEASE_SPEAK_TO_ME_AGAIN_ONCE_YOU_HAVE                                 = 9183,  -- Please speak to me again once you have accepted %. I will then judge whether or not you meet the requirements.
        YOU_HAVE_ACCEPTED_YES_THEN_LET_ME_CHECK                                = 9184,  -- You have accepted %, yes? Then let me check my materials here...
        CONGRATULATIONS_YOU_ARE_QUALIFIED_TO_BE_A_MENTOR                       = 9185,  -- Congratulations! You are qualified to be a mentor!
        MY_MATERIALS_HERE_SAY_THAT_YOU_DON_T                                   = 9186,  -- My materials here say that you don't meet the requirements. Keep at it!
        WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_SERVE_AS_A_MENTOR                                    = 9187,  -- Would you like to serve as a mentor? Yes. No.
        YOU_ARE_NOW_A_REGISTERED_MENTOR                                        = 9188,  -- You are now a registered mentor.
        YOU_CAN_ENABLE_MENTOR_STATUS_BY_USING_THE                              = 9189,  -- You can enable "Mentor Status" by using the command /mentor on. You can disable the status by using /mentor off.
        MENTOR_STATUS_CAN_ALSO_BE_SWITCHED_ON_AND                              = 9190,  -- Mentor status can also be switched on and off in the Config menu found within the Help Desk.
        YOU_ARE_ALREADY_A_REGISTERED_MENTOR                                    = 9191,  -- You are already a registered mentor.
        A_NEW_OBJECTIVE_HAS_BEEN_ADDED_TO_RECORDS                              = 9192,  -- A new objective, %, has been added to Records of Eminence.
        SO_YOU_TOO_HAVE_DECIDED_TO_JOIN_THE                                    = 9193,  -- %! So you, too, have decided to join the Bastokan forces and participate in Conflict!
        HA_HA_DO_NOT_TELL_ME_YOU_ARE                                           = 9194,  -- Ha ha! Do not tell me you are worried about those cowards to the east or those arrogant fools to the north. They will be no match for the strength of our nation. Now let us go and report to the president.
        SIR_I_HAVE_WITH_ME_AN_ADVENTURER_WHO                                   = 9195,  -- Sir! I have with me an adventurer who wishes to participate in...
        WHAT_IN_ALTANA_S_NAME_WAS_THAT_VOLKER                                  = 9196,  -- What in Altana's name was that Volker thinking!? Agreeing to the reinstatement of Conflict... Why am I forced to work with complete idiots!?
        SIR_CAPTAIN_VOLKER_WAS_ONLY_THINKING_OF_THE                            = 9197,  -- Sir, Captain Volker was only thinking of the Republican Army when he made his decision. Conflict would give our forces a boost in morale, as well as sharpen their skills.
        AND_I_M_SAYING_THAT_HIS_WAY_OF                                         = 9198,  -- And I'm saying that his way of thinking is flawed and outdated! Why waste our funds on children's games when that gil could be used to develop new weapons!
        SIR_ARE_YOU_SAYING_THAT_OUR_COUNTRY_WOULD                              = 9199,  -- Sir, are you saying that our country would not profit from Conflict...?
        AND_WHAT_WOULD_A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_KNOW_ABOUT                          = 9200,  -- And what would a Mythril Musketeer know about profit!? That profit is what fills your cupboards with brown bread and rocksalt.
        DON_T_YOU_TELL_ME_HOW_TO_RUN                                           = 9201,  -- Don't you tell me how to run my country! It is my job to decide what will and will not benefit this nation.
        LISTEN_UP_BECAUSE_I_M_ONLY_GOING_TO                                    = 9202,  -- Listen up, because I'm only going to say this once. Conflict is nothing but a series of war games. We are not allowed to even test our new ships or cannons.
        NO_THE_EXERCISES_MUST_BE_WON_WITH_WELL                                 = 9203,  -- No! The exercises must be won with well-planned tactics. In the field of battle tactics, there isn't a nation in all of Vana'diel that can outmatch our generals. There is no reason for us to have to prove that.
        SAN_D_ORIA_HAH_LET_THEM_LINE_UP                                        = 9204,  -- San d'Oria? Hah! Let them line up in their little lines and charge with their wooden spears.
        DON_T_FORGET_THAT_IT_WASN_T_ONLY                                       = 9205,  -- Don't forget that it wasn't only our cannons that delivered them defeat during the Battle of Konschtat.
        AND_WINDURST_HAH_THOSE_COWARDS_DON_T_EVEN                              = 9206,  -- And Windurst? Hah! Those cowards don't even know how to fight! Hiding behind hired mercenaries, muttering spells doesn't win campaigns.
        IT_DIDN_T_WORK_IN_ELSHIMO_AND_IT                                       = 9207,  -- It didn't work in Elshimo and it won't work this time, either! They should all just crawl up in their big tree and hibernate for the winter.
        THE_AGES_OF_STRENGTH_AND_MAGIC_ARE_OVER                                = 9208,  -- The ages of strength and magic are over.
        SAN_D_ORIA_AND_WINDURST_HAVE_THE_TOOLS                                 = 9209,  -- San d'Oria and Windurst have the tools they need to win, but they don't have the brains to use them! Our citizens do. And that's why we will always be victorious!
        SIR_THIS_ADVENTURER                                                    = 9210,  -- Sir, this adventurer...
        YOU_WANT_MY_APPROVAL_TO_FIGHT_IN_CONFLICT                              = 9211,  -- You want my approval to fight in Conflict, citizen? You have it! Dismissed!
        I_APOLOGIZE_FOR_THE_PRESIDENT_S_BEHAVIOR_WHILE                         = 9212,  -- I apologize for the president's behavior. While he is vocal in his opposition to Bastok's participation in Conflict, the last thing he wishes is the Republic's defeat.
        HMMM_SO_YOU_ARE_HERE_FROM_TO_RECEIVE                                   = 9213,  -- Hmmm... So, you are here from [San d'Oria/Windurst] to receive permission to participate in Conflict?
        ID_9214                                                                = 9214,  -- ...
        I_APOLOGIZE_IF_I_LOOK_SHOCKED_BUT_I                                    = 9215,  -- ... I apologize if I look shocked, but I expected more from [the once mighty lions of San d'Oria/the once mighty magicians of the Federation]...
        WELL_NO_MATTER_FOLLOW_ME_WE_MUST_NOT                                   = 9216,  -- Well, no matter. Follow me. We must not keep the president waiting.
        SIR_I_HAVE_WITH_ME_AN_ADVENTURER_WHO_2                                 = 9217,  -- Sir! I have with me an adventurer who wishes to participate in...
        I_HAVE_A_QUESTION_FOR_YOU_YOUNG_MAN                                    = 9218,  -- I have a question for you, young man/young lady]. Why did you pledge your allegiance to [San d'Oria/Windurst] and not to Bastok?
        YOU_CHOSE_BECAUSE_OF_ITS_PEOPLE_ITS_CULTURE                            = 9219,  -- You chose [San d'Oria/Windurst] because of... ...its people. ...its culture. ...its city. ...its leader.
        ITS_PEOPLE_THE_HELPLESS_MASSES_WHINING_FOR_A                           = 9220,  -- Its people? The helpless masses whining for a hero to hold their hands when things get tough? The petty common folk, blind to their own worthlessness? Did you really think that you could be their hero?
        SAN_D_ORIA_S_CULTURE_YOU_MEAN_THEIR                                    = 9221,  -- San d'Oria's culture? You mean their stubborn pride? Or perhaps the blatant ostentation found in their castles and cathedrals? But, tell me. Can a well-decorated chateau feed the hungry masses!?
        WINDURST_S_CULTURE_YES_MAGIC_IS_GOOD_FOR                               = 9222,  -- Windurst's culture? Yes, magic is good for talent shows and birthday parties, but can an incantation feed your nation's starving people!?
        ITS_CITY_HAVE_YOU_SPENT_EVEN_A_SECOND                                  = 9223,  -- Its city? Have you spent even a second to think of what the people of your nation had to give to build that city for its leaders? Years of sweat and blood...and for what? Can a fancy bridge or beautiful fountain feed the hungry masses!?
