        IF_I_TRIED_TO_TAKE_MY_BABY_UP                                          = 9695,  -- If I tried to take my baby, [/Ultra /Hyper /Psycho /Eternal /Neo /Lovely /Pretty /Final /Extra /Deadly /Savage /Aero /Pseudo /Universal /Exciting /Celestial /Super /Mighty /Mega /Omni /Poly ][/Terror /Perfect /Royale /Gorgeous /Pretty /Hell /Fantasy /Stealth /Powerful /Invincible /Explosive /Storm /Fantastic /Duper /Go-Go /Morphing /Retro /Sonic /Cloud /Sky /Stellar ][/Hyper /Neo /Lovely /Happy /Caller /Hound /XI /Armored /Brutal /Buster /Alpha /Chief /Provoker /Mincer /Streak /King /Prince /Power /Robo /Delver /Mystic ][C.I.D./Enterprise/Nautilus/Gilgamemnon/Redwing/Blackjack/Falcon/Highwind/Ragnarok/Hilda Garde/Prima Vista/Red Rose/Fahrenheit], up there in her current state, she'd be torn to pieces in the turbulence.
        NO_THERE_S_A_FEW_MORE_THINGS_I                                         = 9696,  -- No, there's a few more things I've got to teach her before we have our date in the heavens.
        EXCELLENT_WHEN_DO_YOU_THINK_SHE_WILL_BE                                = 9697,  -- Excellent! When do you think she will be ready?
        HOLD_YOUR_HORSES_THERE_LOUVERANCE_I_M_WORKING                          = 9698,  -- Hold your horses there, Louverance. I'm working as fast as I can. I have some of the best craftsmen in Vana'diel on the project.
        AND_UNTIL_WE_RE_DONE_WE_NEED_YOU                                       = 9699,  -- And until we're done, we need you back in Movalpolos keeping an eye on those Moblins. Do you think you can handle that?
        AND_UNTIL_WE_RE_DONE_WE_NEED_YOU_2                                     = 9700,  -- And until we're done, we need you back in Movalpolos keeping an eye on those Moblins. Do you think you can handle that?
        YOU_NEED_NOT_WORRY_MASTER_CID_JABBOS_HAS                               = 9701,  -- You need not worry, Master Cid. Jabbos has provided me with much information on his subterranean companions.
        AND_A_FEW_OF_MY_FRIENDS_WILL_ALSO                                      = 9702,  -- And a few of my...friends will also be lending their hands.
        I_KNOW_EVERYTHING_ABOUT_MOVALPOLOS_I_KNOW_EVERYTHING                   = 9703,  -- I know...everything about...Movalpolos... I know everything...about Moblins...
        ALRIGHT_THEN_IT_LOOKS_LIKE_I_VE_FOUND                                  = 9704,  -- Alright then. It looks like I've found the right men for the job.
        BY_THE_WAY_HAVE_YOU_HEARD_ANYTHING_REGARDING                           = 9705,  -- By the way, have you heard anything regarding Lady Prishe?
        WHILE_SEARCHING_FOR_INFORMATION_ON_AL_TAIEU_I                          = 9706,  -- While searching for information on Al'Taieu, I learned of a group of Mithra known as sin hunters.
        I_AM_NOT_SURE_OF_THE_DETAILS_BUT                                       = 9707,  -- I am not sure of the details, but I believe they originally traveled from their Mithran homeland to catch Cardinal Mildaurion and punish her for her past crimes.
        HOWEVER_NOW_THAT_THE_THREE_BELIEVE_THAT_THE                            = 9708,  -- However, now that the three believe that the Cardinal is dead, they search for Prishe to have her atone for the sins of Mildaurion.
        THAT_S_RIDICULOUS_HOW_DO_THEY_THINK_THAT                               = 9709,  -- That's ridiculous! How do they think that they can get away with something so crazy!?
        WE_CAN_ONLY_HOPE_THAT_ULMIA_FINDS_PRISHE                               = 9710,  -- We can only hope that Ulmia finds Prishe in San d'Oria before the Mithran Trackers do...
        AND_THEN_THERE_S_TENZEN_NO_WORD_FROM                                   = 9711,  -- And then there's Tenzen. No word from him either...
        HE_SAID_HE_WAS_HEADING_TO_THE_LA                                       = 9712,  -- He said he was heading to the La Theine Plateau to ask the terrestrial avatar Carbuncle for help, but...
        COULD_YOU_TRY_AND_FIND_OUT_WHAT_HAPPENED                               = 9713,  -- %. Could you try and find out what happened to Ulmia and Tenzen?
        THEY_COULD_BE_IN_SOME_REAL_TROUBLE_WE                                  = 9714,  -- They could be in some real trouble. We're counting on you!
        SIN_HUNTERS_MAYBE_THEY_TOO_ARE_THINKING_PRISHE                         = 9715,  -- Sin hunters... Maybe they, too, are thinking Prishe is the cause of all this...
        MASTER_CID_WHAT_ARE_YOU_IMPLYING                                       = 9716,  -- Master Cid, what are you implying?
        HM_I_LL_CALL_TENZEN_BACK_FROM_JEUNO                                    = 9717,  -- Hm... I'll call Tenzen back from Jeuno and have him head for Movalpolos.
        THE_THINGS_HE_TOLD_US_WERE_UNBELIEVABLE_YOU                            = 9718,  -- The things he told us were unbelievable. You've got to hear them for yourself.
        WE_HAVE_TO_FIND_PRISHE_AS_SOON_AS                                      = 9719,  -- %, we have to find Prishe as soon as possible. That's why I want you to head for San d'Oria and help Ulmia in her search.
        GOOD_LUCK_AND_MAY_ALTANA_BE_WITH_YOU                                   = 9720,  -- Good luck, and may Altana be with you.
        HMMM_ULMIA_JUST_CAME_BY_A_FEW_DAYS                                     = 9721,  -- Hmmm... Ulmia just came by a few days ago with a few of those trackers. They said they had found Prishe, but that she had got away before they could...finish their business.
        THEY_ALSO_SAID_THAT_WHEN_SHE_ESCAPED_SHE                               = 9722,  -- They also said that when she escaped, she took a large chunk of magicite known as the Star of Tavnazia with her. You wouldn't happen to know anything about that, would you?
        THE_STAR_OF_TAVNAZIA_IT_WAS_SAID_TO                                    = 9723,  -- The Star of Tavnazia... It was said to have been lost twenty years ago during the Great War... You say that Lady Prishe possesses it!?
        BUT_WHERE_COULD_SHE_HAVE_RUN_OFF_TO                                    = 9724,  -- But where could she have run off to...?
        AND_THAT_S_EXACTLY_WHY_WE_RE_STUCK                                     = 9725,  -- And that's exactly why we're stuck like a chocobo in the mud. Ulmia hasn't slept for days, the poor child.
        WELL_ALL_WE_CAN_DO_KNOW_IS_WAIT                                        = 9726,  -- Well, all we can do know is wait for Tenzen to come back and pray that he has found something.
        TENZEN_SAID_HE_WAS_HEADING_FOR_THE_LA                                  = 9727,  -- %, Tenzen said he was heading for the La Theine Plateau to find Carbuncle. Why don't you try joining him?
        MASTER_CID_HAS_LADY_ULMIA_RETURNED_AND_WHAT                            = 9728,  -- Master Cid! Has Lady Ulmia returned!? And what of Lady Prishe!?
        WHOA_CALM_DOWN_NOW_WHY_DON_T_YOU                                       = 9729,  -- Whoa, calm down, now. Why don't you tell us what happened...
        CALM_DOWN_CALM_DOWN_ULMIA_ARRIVED_BACK_HERE                            = 9730,  -- Calm down. Calm down. Ulmia arrived back here a few days ago. She's resting in one of our guest residences. Prishe... Well, there are still no signs of her... But before we set out to look for her, why don't you tell us what you found out on your journey.
        THE_TERRESTRIAL_AVATARS_TOLD_YOU_THAT_IT_S                             = 9731,  -- The terrestrial avatars told you that? It's so hard to believe, but...
        SOME_OF_THE_THINGS_NAG_MOLADA_SAID_DO                                  = 9732,  -- Some of the things Nag'molada said do make some sense.
        FOR_EXAMPLE_THE_RECENT_STRANGE_ENERGY_READINGS_FROM                    = 9733,  -- For example, the recent strange energy readings from the crags. I've studied those as well.
        BUT_I_NEVER_IMAGINED_THAT_THE_REMNANTS_OF                              = 9734,  -- But I never imagined that the remnants of the ancients were trying to do something as crazy as that--using the lines to converge the energy from all five crystals...
        AND_ULTIMATELY_USE_THAT_CONCENTRATED_POWER_TO_OPEN                     = 9735,  -- ...and ultimately use that concentrated power to open the Gates of Paradise...
        HMMM_I_M_NOT_POSITIVE_BUT_WITH_THAT                                    = 9736,  -- Hmmm... I'm not positive, but with that much energy, opening the gates may not be as impossible as it sounds.
        AND_WITH_ALL_THE_TECHNOLOGY_THOSE_HOODED_SCIENTISTS                    = 9737,  -- And with all the technology those hooded scientists in Jeuno have...
        BUT_WAIT_A_MINUTE_DIDN_T_THEY_ALREADY                                  = 9738,  -- But wait a minute. Didn't they already try opening the gates ten thousand years ago...and fail miserably? Just look at their capital! It sunk to the bottom of the sea.
        UNTIL_WE_FIND_OUT_WHAT_THIS_PARADISE_PLACE                             = 9739,  -- Until we find out what this Paradise place really is, we can't let the Zilart go on doing as they please.
        THAT_IS_TRUE_BUT_WE_FIRST_MUST_FACE                                    = 9740,  -- That is true, but we first must face the problem that lies before us--the Keeper of the Apocalypse!
        I_WAS_CERTAIN_THAT_SELH_TEUS_WAS_THE                                   = 9741,  -- I was certain that Selh'teus was the one we were searching for, but after hearing the testimony of Fenrir...
        THAT_THE_KEEPER_OF_THE_APOCALYPSE_WOULD_BE                             = 9742,  -- That the Keeper of the Apocalypse would be born unto Tavnazia...
        TENZEN_ACCORDING_TO_WHAT_YOU_VE_TOLD_ME                                = 9743,  -- Tenzen. According to what you've told me, Prishe's treatment in Tavnazia was quite out of the ordinary.
        ARE_YOU_TRYING_TO_SAY_THAT_THIS_IS                                     = 9744,  -- Are you trying to say that this is because...she is the keeper?
        WHILE_IT_PAINS_ME_TO_BELIEVE_SO_ALL                                    = 9745,  -- While it pains me to believe so, all the recent events seem to point to that conclusion. I have asked Phoenix numerous times for an answer, but she only replies that she, too, does not know...
        BUT_IF_IT_IS_TRUE_IF_PRISHE_IS                                         = 9746,  -- But if it is true--if Prishe is the Keeper of the Apocalypse...then there is only one thing I can do...
        HOLD_ON_TENZEN_WE_STILL_DON_T_KNOW                                     = 9747,  -- Hold on, Tenzen! We still don't know for sure that she's the one!
        YEAH_SHE_S_A_LITTLE_RUDE_AND_A                                         = 9748,  -- Yeah, she's a little rude, and a little crude, and a heck of a lot wilder than I like most of my company. But once you get past that, you realize that she's one of the most honest people you'll ever meet. I couldn't imagine her lying to a soul, let alone be untrue to herself.
        TENZEN_YOU_CAN_T_TRULY_BELIEVE_THAT_SHE                                = 9749,  -- Tenzen, you can't truly believe that she's inherited the will of Promathia, can you?
        HOWEVER_I_CANNOT_DOUBT_WHAT_I_SAW_I                                    = 9750,  -- However, I cannot doubt what I saw. I believe that Fenrir showed me what he did for a reason.
        IT_IS_THE_SOLE_WISH_OF_THE_TERRESTRIAL                                 = 9751,  -- It is the sole wish of the terrestrial avatars to keep the Gates of Paradise closed. Anyone who attempts to open the gates will undoubtedly become their enemy.
        PERHAPS_THE_WILL_OF_PROMATHIA_REMAINS_DORMANT_WITHIN                   = 9752,  -- Perhaps the will of Promathia remains dormant within Lady Prishe. Perhaps she simply has not realized that she carries the seed of twilight.
        ID_9753                                                                = 9753,  -- ...
        WELL_THERE_S_ONE_WAY_TO_FIND_OUT                                       = 9754,  -- Well, there's one way to find out--and that's finding Prishe.
        WE_CAN_DECIDE_WHAT_TO_DO_THEN_EVEN                                     = 9755,  -- We can decide what to do then...even if that involves...
        I_WANT_YOU_TO_HEAD_FOR_SAN_D                                           = 9756,  -- %, I want you to head for San d'Oria and check up on Ulmia.
        IT_ALSO_WORRIES_ME_HOW_WE_HAVEN_T                                      = 9757,  -- It also worries me how we haven't heard anything from Louverance as well...
        HE_SAID_HE_WAS_GOING_TO_TRY_TO                                         = 9758,  -- He said he was going to try to gather information on the celestial capital of Al'Taieu, but...
        I_WILL_TRAVEL_TO_JEUNO_AND_INVESTIGATE_THE                             = 9759,  -- I will travel to Jeuno and investigate the situation there. If the Duchy were to find Prishe before we do...
        FAREWELL_MASTER_CID                                                    = 9760,  -- Farewell, Master Cid.
        AHEM_WE_DO_HAVE_SOME_GOOD_NEWS_FOR                                     = 9761,  -- Ahem! We do have some good news for you, though, Tenzen. It sounds like Louverance was able to find Selh'teus.
        ON_TOP_OF_THAT_WE_ALSO_MAY_HAVE                                        = 9762,  -- On top of that, we also may have found a way to get to the fifth mothercrystal under the North Sea.
        YOU_HAVE_WHAT                                                          = 9763,  -- You have what!?
        IF_YOU_WANT_THE_DETAILS_YOU_SHOULD_GO                                  = 9764,  -- If you want the details, you should go talk with Louverance yourself.
        RAIBAHT_WOULD_YOU_TELL_TENZEN_WHERE_HE_CAN                             = 9765,  -- Raibaht, would you tell Tenzen where he can find his companions?
        ALRIGHT_BUT_I_M_GOING_TO_HAVE_TO                                       = 9766,  -- Alright. But I'm going to have to ask you to refrain from questioning Ulmia until Louverance gets back. We don't want to jump to any conclusions before we've grasped the whole picture.
        TENZEN_I_UNDERSTAND_THAT_YOU_BLAME_YOURSELF_FOR                        = 9767,  -- Tenzen. I understand that you blame yourself for not being able to find Prishe, but think of poor Ulmia and how she would react.
        VERY_WELL_MASTER_CID_I_PROMISE_I_WILL                                  = 9768,  -- Very well, Master Cid. I promise I will not speak of what I saw to lady Ulmia until the return of Sir Louverance.
        IF_IT_IS_NOT_TOO_MUCH_TO_ASK                                           = 9769,  -- If it is not too much to ask, might I inquire as to where she is staying?
        RAIBAHT_SHOW_TENZEN_TO_ULMIA_S_ROOM                                    = 9770,  -- Raibaht, show Tenzen to Ulmia's room.
        TO_TELL_YOU_THE_TRUTH_I_THINK_WE                                       = 9771,  -- %... To tell you the truth, I think we may be in way over our heads here...
        UP_UNTIL_NOW_WHETHER_IT_BE_FOR_SCIENCE                                 = 9772,  -- Up until now, whether it be for science or justice, I've never thought too deeply about what I was getting into--I just took the ball and ran with it as fast as I could. But this time... This time a little voice in the back of my head is telling me that I should be careful. I don't know. Maybe I'm just getting old.
        IT_S_THOSE_ANCIENTS_THAT_YOU_KEEP_TALKING                              = 9773,  -- It's those ancients that you keep talking about. If they're rooted firmly in Jeuno, there may not be anything we can do to pull them out.
        FIGHTING_WYRMS_AND_BEASTMEN_IS_BAD_ENOUGH_I                            = 9774,  -- Fighting wyrms and beastmen is bad enough. I shudder to think what would happen if the Duchy's army was thrown into the mix...
        AND_THERE_S_SOMETHING_ELSE_THAT_HAS_BEEN                               = 9775,  -- And there's something else that has been bothering me.
        THIS_FAR_EASTERN_COUNTRY_THAT_TENZEN_HAS_SUPPOSEDLY                    = 9776,  -- This Far Eastern country that Tenzen has supposedly traveled from... Even the pirates of Norg know little about it. How do we know if we can really trust him...?
        WHO_SPEAKS_THE_TRUTH_AND_WHO_PEDDLES_LIES                              = 9777,  -- Who speaks the truth and who peddles lies? It is becoming harder and harder to tell. I see a storm brewing on our horizon. If we don't take care, our ship may sink, and everything we have fought for up to now may be lost.
        IF_YOU_REALLY_WANT_TO_SAVE_YOUR_NATION                                 = 9778,  -- If you really want to save your nation and its people, you have to be strong. See things with your own eyes; make decisions with your own heart. Don't be fooled by those with ulterior motives.
        OH_SORRY_ABOUT_THAT_I_DIDN_T_MEAN                                      = 9779,  -- Oh, sorry about that, %. I didn't mean to sound like a father scolding his son/daughter].
        HM_WHAT_S_WRONG                                                        = 9780,  -- Hm? What's wrong?
        LOUVERANCE_MENTIONED_HE_WAS_GOING_TO_BEGIN_HIS                         = 9781,  -- Louverance mentioned he was going to begin his search for Al'Taieu in Tavnazia.
        IF_YOU_HURRY_YOU_MIGHT_BE_ABLE_TO                                      = 9782,  -- If you hurry, you might be able to catch up with him.
        AND_I_KNOW_I_JUST_TOLD_YOU_TO                                          = 9783,  -- And I know I just told you to make decisions with your own heart, but I think that another good thing for you to do right now is find Prishe...
        ULMIA_SAID_THAT_SHE_WAS_GOING_TO_SAN                                   = 9784,  -- Ulmia said that she was going to San d'Oria to look for her. Why don't you go and see if she found anything?
        IF_PRISHE_IS_THE_ABHORRENT_ONE_LIKE_TENZEN                             = 9785,  -- If Prishe is the abhorrent one like Tenzen says she is, then our only key to saving her will be Ulmia.
        HURRY_I_DON_T_THINK_THAT_WE_HAVE                                       = 9786,  -- Hurry, %. I don't think that we have much more time. We have to get to Prishe before...
        ULMIA_WHO_IS_THAT_WITH_YOU_THEY_RE                                     = 9787,  -- Ulmia!? Who is that with you? They're not...
        YES_THEY_ARE_THE_MITHRAN_SIN_HUNTERS_THE                               = 9788,  -- Yes, they are the Mithran sin hunters--the trackers who have come to our land to find Prishe.
        MITHRAN_SIN_HUNTERS_THEN_PRISHE_HAS_ALREADY_BEEN                       = 9789,  -- Mithran sin hunters! Then Prishe has already been...punished!?
        OF_COURSE_NOT_MASTER_CID_HOWEVER_WE_WERE                               = 9790,  -- Of course not, Master Cid! However, we were able to find her!
        BUT_NOW_SHE_IS_GONE_AGAIN_AND_SHE                                      = 9791,  -- But now she is gone again... And she took the magicite with her!
        ULMIA_HM_AND_WHO_MIGHT_THESE_THREE_BE                                  = 9792,  -- Ulmia!? Hm? And who might these three be?
        THEY_ARE_THE_MITHRAN_TRACKERS_SIN_HUNTERS_WHO                          = 9793,  -- They are the Mithran Trackers--sin hunters who have come from the Mithran homeland to find...Prishe.
        SIN_HUNTERS_WHAT_DID_PRISHE_EVER_DO_TO                                 = 9794,  -- Sin hunters! What did Prishe ever do to the Mithra!? Wait, does this mean you found her?
        YES_WE_WERE_ABLE_TO_LOCATE_HER                                         = 9795,  -- Yes, we were able to locate her.
        HOWEVER_SHE_WENT_OFF_ON_HER_OWN_AGAIN                                  = 9796,  -- However, she went off on her own again...with the magicite...
        THE_MAGICITE_FILL_ME_IN_ON_THE_DETAILS                                 = 9797,  -- The magicite! Fill me in on the details, Ulmia.
        I_SEE_I_DIDN_T_REALIZE_THAT_TAVNAZIA                                   = 9798,  -- I see... I didn't realize that Tavnazia's magicite was that powerful...or that dangerous.
        SO_IT_WAS_THE_ENERGY_FROM_THAT_STONE                                   = 9799,  -- So, it was the energy from that stone that affected the members of the Multinational Expedition--it invaded their hearts and minds, ultimately driving them to do the unspeakable.
        EXACTLY_OUR_COUNTRY_S_RRREPRESENTATIVE_ON_THAT_EXPEDITION              = 9800,  -- Exactly. Our country's rrrepresentative on that expedition found a shard of magicite and brought it back to our homeland. It was then that we, too, realized its terrifying power.
        HOWEVER_WE_WERE_NEVER_TOLD_WHERE_THAT_SHARD                            = 9801,  -- However, we were never told where that shard came from. Further Mithran expeditions were sent to the Northlands to investigate the stone's origins, but they were unsuccessful.
        NO_IT_WAS_A_COMPLETELY_DIFFERENT_INVESTIGATION_THAT                    = 9802,  -- No, it was a completely different investigation that led us to the answer. While searching for the rrrelic of the dragon stolen from the Temple of Uggalepih, we found what we were looking for.
        YOU_YOU_MET_WITH_PRISHE_AND_CARDINAL_MILDAURION                        = 9803,  -- You... You met with Prishe and Cardinal Mildaurion in the Tavnazian Cathedral?
        AFTER_A_BIT_OF_PERSUASION_THE_CARDINAL_SHOWED                          = 9804,  -- After a bit of...persuasion, the cardinal showed us what they called the Star of Tavnazia. In other words--magicite.
        WE_TOLD_HER_OF_THE_TERRIBLE_POWER_THAT                                 = 9805,  -- We told her of the terrible power that the magicite contained, and demanded that she dispose of it somewhere it would never be seen again.
        HOWEVER_THE_CARDINAL_WOULD_NOT_LISTEN_TO_RRREASON                      = 9806,  -- However, the cardinal would not listen to rrreason.
        SHE_WOULD_ONLY_SAY_THAT_THE_STONE_WAS                                  = 9807,  -- She would only say that the stone was necessary to wake the gods from their eternal slumber.
        WAKE_THE_GODS_BUT_THAT_S                                               = 9808,  -- Wake the gods...? But that's...!
        I_COULD_NOT_BRING_MYSELF_TO_BELIEVE_MISS                               = 9809,  -- I could not bring myself to believe Miss Shikaree's words, either. Not until I heard the same story from the San d'Orian Cathedral...
        THE_HYMNS_THE_TAVNAZIAN_CHOIR_WOULD_SING_THEIR                         = 9810,  -- The hymns the Tavnazian choir would sing... Their words possessed the power to bring the gods back to life.
        A_STONE_A_SONG                                                         = 9811,  -- A stone... A song...
        WAIT_THAT_SONG_PRISHE_SANG_TO_HELP_SELH                                = 9812,  -- Wait! That song Prishe sang to help Selh'teus escape. Is that the same song?
        AND_SO_THE_WHOLE_SONG_HAS_BEEN_RECITED                                 = 9813,  -- And so, the whole song has been recited...?
        NO_THERE_IS_A_FIFTH_VERSE_AND_ONLY                                     = 9814,  -- No. There is a fifth verse...and only the sleeping gods know it.
        HOWEVER_IF_ONE_WERE_TO_INQUIRE_WITH_THE                                = 9815,  -- However, if one were to inquire with the god that recently awoke in the Uleguerand Range, it is only a matter of time before the fifth and final verse is sung.
        OR_POSSIBLY_THE_WOMAN_IN_SEL_NO_I                                      = 9816,  -- Or possibly the woman in Sel-- No, I cannot trust you yet with that information. Good day.
        MASTER_CID_I_WISH_TO_CONTINUE_MY_SEARCH                                = 9817,  -- Master Cid, I wish to continue my search for Prishe with the three Mithran Trackers.
        WHOA_HOLD_ON_THERE_ULMIA_THE_TRACKERS_ARE                              = 9818,  -- Whoa, hold on there, Ulmia. The trackers are only looking for Prishe so they can...you know...punish her.
        TO_ENSURE_HER_SAFETY_WE_HAVE_TO_FIND                                   = 9819,  -- To ensure her safety, we have to find Prishe before those frisky felines do.
        THIS_IS_JUST_BETWEEN_YOU_AND_ME_BUT                                    = 9820,  -- (This is just between you and me, but I've already talked things over with some of my...acquaintances in the Tenshodo and Norg. They're scouring the continent for any information on our blue-haired princess. If they find anything, we'll be the first to know. That's why you need to stick around--so you can be here when that info comes in.)
        THANK_YOU_MASTER_CID_FOR_EVERYTHING                                    = 9821,  -- Thank you, Master Cid...for everything...
        AND_TO_TOP_THAT_OFF_WE_VE_GOT                                          = 9822,  -- And to top that off, we've got a first-class adventurer on our side. Isn't that right, %?
        HE_S_SHE_S_GOING_TO_GO_FIND                                            = 9823,  -- He's/She's] going to go find out if Louverance has discovered anything of interest.
        I_M_STILL_NOT_TOO_SURE_WHY_PRISHE                                      = 9824,  -- I'm still not too sure why Prishe would just run off with that fragment of the Star of Tavnazia, but I'll bet my apron that it has something to do with that Cardinal Mildaurion.
        LOUVERANCE_SAID_HE_WAS_LOOKING_FOR_THE_CARDINAL                        = 9825,  -- %. Louverance said he was looking for the cardinal. Maybe he knows something that could be of use. If you hurry, you might be able to catch up with him.
        I_M_STILL_NOT_TOO_SURE_WHY_PRISHE_2                                    = 9826,  -- I'm still not too sure why Prishe would just run off with that fragment of the Star of Tavnazia, but I'll bet my apron that it has something to do with that boy, Selh'teus.
        IF_TENZEN_RETURNS_AND_WE_CAN_CATCH_THIS                                = 9827,  -- If Tenzen returns and we can catch this so-called Keeper of the Apocalypse in Movalpolos, the clouds covering this mystery we're knee-deep in just might clear up.
        TENZEN_SAID_HE_WAS_HEADING_TO_THE_LA                                   = 9828,  -- %, Tenzen said he was heading to the La Theine Plateau to find Carbuncle. If you hurry, you might be able to meet up with him.
        RAIBAHT_TAKE_ULMIA_TO_CORNELIA_S_QUARTERS_AND                          = 9829,  -- Raibaht, take Ulmia to Cornelia's quarters and have the president's daughter prepare a room for our guest.
        YES_SIR_3                                                              = 9830,  -- Yes, sir...
