        HM_DID_MY_MASTER_HAVE_ANY_PARTICULAR_PLACE                             = 10797,  -- Hm? Did my master have any particular place he preferred to be?
        NOW_THAT_YOU_MENTION_IT_HE_AND_GUMBAH                                  = 10798,  -- Now that you mention it, he and Gumbah often used to travel to Grauberg.
        WHAT_WAS_IT_ABOUT_THAT_MOUNTAIN                                        = 10799,  -- What was it about that mountain...?
        YES_YOU_NEED_SOMETHING_I_VE_NO_TIME                                    = 10800,  -- Yes? You need something? I've no time for idle chitchat.
        SON_OF_A_HEXAGUN_ARE_THOSE_WHAT_IN                                     = 10801,  -- Son of a hexagun! Are those %? What in the Goddess's name are you doing with those?
        I_SEE_I_SEE_BULLETS_TO_BLAST_THROUGH                                   = 10802,  -- I see, I see. Bullets to blast through magic armor, you say?
        YOU_WOULDN_T_HAPPEN_TO_BE_LOOKIN_FOR                                   = 10803,  -- You wouldn't happen to be lookin' for something like the old % they used back in the Great War, would you?
        AHH_STIRS_UP_MEMORIES_IN_THIS_OLD_GALKA                                = 10804,  -- Ahh...stirs up memories in this old Galka's soul, it does. After the war ended, I never thought I'd hear the name again.
        GODDESS_ONLY_KNOWS_WHAT_YOU_D_WANT_WITH                                = 10805,  -- Goddess only knows what you'd want with those old things...but yes, I think I could do it for you. There's just one catch. The casting process requires some rather...rare...ingredients.
        AND_TO_BE_EXACT                                                        = 10806,  -- % and %, to be exact.
        PROVIDE_ME_WITH_WHAT_I_NEED_AND_THE                                    = 10807,  -- Provide me with what I need, and the job is as good as done.
        WHERE_TO_FIND_THEM_YOU_ASK_I_HAVEN                                     = 10808,  -- Where to find them, you ask? I haven't a clue. They say there was once a plentiful supply in North Gustaberg, but it was exhausted completely by the war's end...
        PROVIDE_ME_WITH_THE_MATERIALS_I_NEED_AND                               = 10809,  -- Provide me with the materials I need, and your job is as good as done.
        WHERE_TO_FIND_THEM_I_HAVEN_T_A                                         = 10810,  -- Where to find them...? I haven't a clue. I hear they used to be plentiful in North Gustaberg, but the supply was surely exhausted years ago...
        OH_HO_WELL_LOOK_AT_THIS_IT_SEEMS                                       = 10811,  -- Oh ho, well look at this! It seems I underestimated you. Well, a promise is a promise...one order of beastman-blasting bullets, coming right up!
        GOOD_CRAFTSMANSHIP_TAKES_TIME_BUT_I_LL_BE                              = 10812,  -- Good craftsmanship takes time, but I'll be done before you know it. Why don't you head to the Markets and try to catch yourself a gold carp or two while you wait?
        DON_T_YOU_KNOW_BETTER_THAN_TO_RUSH                                     = 10813,  -- Don't you know better than to rush a master at work? Just a bit longer, I say!
        I_WAS_WONDERING_WHEN_YOU_D_COME_BACK                                   = 10814,  -- I was wondering when you'd come back. Here you are, one order of %, just like we used to make 'em!
        I_EVEN_TOOK_THE_LIBERTY_OF_MAKING_A                                    = 10815,  -- I even took the liberty of making a few improvements to the old recipe. One blast from these and even the most potent magical armor will be reduced to little more than scrap metal.
        MY_FEE_HAH_DON_T_MENTION_IT_I                                          = 10816,  -- My fee? Hah! Don't mention it! I haven't enjoyed my work this much in years. If you come across any other curiosities, you know where to find me!
        PRESS_BUTTON_TO_PROCEED                                                = 10817,  -- Press button to proceed.
        GREETINGS_FRIEND_I_AM_REGISTRAR_CLOUD_WALKER_MY                        = 10818,  -- Greetings, friend. I am Registrar Cloud Walker. My duty is to issue marriage certificates to married couples.
        WHAT_CAN_I_DO_FOR_YOU_TODAY                                            = 10819,  -- What can I do for you today?
        THE_MARRIAGE_CERTIFICATE_IS_A_LEGAL_DOCUMENT_ISSUED                    = 10820,  -- The marriage certificate is a legal document issued in recognition of the matrimony of two individuals. It can also be used as a wall decoration for your Mog House.
        COUPLES_WISHING_TO_RECEIVE_THE_CERTIFICATE_MUST_SHOW                   = 10821,  -- Couples wishing to receive the certificate must show proof of their marriage, and this can be done in a number of ways.
        THE_COUPLE_SHOULD_FORM_A_PARTY_WHILE_THE                               = 10822,  -- The couple should form a party while the husband is wearing his matrimony ring, and his wife, her matrimony band. After that, speak to me, and I'll draw up the certificates for you.
        BUT_IF_YOU_POSSESS_A_WEDDING_RING_THE                                  = 10823,  -- But if you possess a wedding ring, the procedure can be completed on your own.
        KEEP_IN_MIND_THOUGH_THAT_YOU_CAN_T                                     = 10824,  -- Keep in mind though, that you can't have more than one certificate at any given time. Also, the nation of issuance for your certificate must be the same as your partner's.
        ONE_LAST_THING_A_MISPLACED_CERTIFICATE_CAN_BE                          = 10825,  -- One last thing. A misplaced certificate can be reissued, but only by the same officiating body that you originally received it from.
        A_WEDDING_IS_A_JOYFUL_OCCASION_IN_WHICH                                = 10826,  -- A wedding is a joyful occasion in which two souls brought together by fate are joined as partners in life.
        IN_BASTOK_IT_S_CUSTOMARY_FOR_THE_BRIDE                                 = 10827,  -- In Bastok, it's customary for the bride and groom to swear an oath of endless love in the presence of witnesses. After which, wedding rings are exchanged.
        TO_CONCLUDE_THE_PROCEEDINGS_ALL_THOSE_PRESENT_JOIN                     = 10828,  -- To conclude the proceedings, all those present join in a toast with bottles of grape juice in hand and share in the newly joined couple's happiness.
        FIRST_OF_ALL_YOU_LL_NEED_TO_PREPARE                                    = 10829,  -- First of all, you'll need to prepare wedding rings--a matrimony ring and a matrimony band, to be precise.
        AS_THEIR_SYNTHESIS_REQUIRES_RARE_HARD_TO_FIND                          = 10830,  -- As their synthesis requires rare, hard-to-find ingredients, there truly is no better token of undying devotion between two people.
        BEFORE_YOU_PRESENT_THE_RING_TO_YOUR_PARTNER                            = 10831,  -- Before you present the ring to your partner, you should consider engraving your name onto it using a cyclone crystal. This practice is widespread among adventurers nowadays.
        YOU_LL_ALSO_FIND_THAT_BENEDIGHT_COATS_AND                              = 10832,  -- You'll also find that benedight coats and wedding dresses are popular as ceremonial attire for men and women, respectively.
        SIMILAR_GARMENTS_EXIST_THAT_CAN_BE_SYNTHESIZED_WHETHER                 = 10833,  -- Similar garments exist that can be synthesized. Whether you perform the synthesis yourself or employ a friend to do so, though, is entirely your decision. Gathering the needed ingredients can be pricey, but it's for this reason they're highly valued.
        THERE_S_NO_NEED_TO_FEEL_DEJECTED_THOUGH                                = 10834,  -- There's no need to feel dejected, though, if they don't fall within your budget. There's no law dictating what couples have to wear at their own wedding, after all.
        IF_YOU_HAVE_TROUBLE_OBTAINING_ANY_OF_THE                               = 10835,  -- If you have trouble obtaining any of the ceremonial items I've mentioned, they can also be purchased from the chests you see here.
        FIREWORKS_WEDDING_BELLS_AND_THE_LIKE_ARE_ALSO                          = 10836,  -- Fireworks, wedding bells, and the like are also available to help add flavor to your special day, so feel free to purchase whatever you need.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_ALREADY_HAVE_A_MARRIAGE                              = 10837,  -- It looks like you already have a marriage certificate in your possession. I'm afraid I'm not authorized to issue you another.
        YOUR_CURRENT_JOB_LEVEL_MUST_BE_LEVEL_OR                                = 10838,  -- Your current job level must be level # or higher if you wish to receive a marriage certificate.
        I_M_AFRAID_I_M_NOT_AUTHORIZED_TO                                       = 10839,  -- I'm afraid I'm not authorized to issue you a marriage certificate.
        MARRIED_COUPLES_WISHING_TO_RECEIVE_MARRIAGE_CERTIFICATES_SHOULD        = 10840,  -- Married couples wishing to receive marriage certificates should form a party while the husband is wearing his matrimony ring, and his wife, her matrimony band. After that, speak to an official in charge, and the certificates will be drawn up for you.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_VE_ALREADY_BEEN_ISSUED                               = 10841,  -- It looks like you've already been issued a marriage certificate by another nation. A misplaced certificate can be reissued, but only by the same officiating body that you originally received it from.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOUR_SPOUSE_S_MARRIAGE_CERTIFICATE                       = 10842,  -- It looks like your spouse's marriage certificate was issued by another nation.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOUR_SPOUSE_S_MARRIAGE_CERTIFICATE_2                     = 10843,  -- It looks like your spouse's marriage certificate was issued by another nation. If you want one of your own, you'll have to speak with the same officiating body that issued your spouse's.
        ACCEPTING_A_MARRIAGE_CERTIFICATE_FROM_OUR_NATION_WILL                  = 10844,  -- Accepting a marriage certificate from our nation will render you ineligible to receive one from another. Also, the nation of issuance for your marriage certificate must be the same as your partner's.
        ACCEPTING_A_MARRIAGE_CERTIFICATE_FROM_OUR_NATION_WILL_2                = 10845,  -- Accepting a marriage certificate from our nation will render you ineligible to receive one from another.
        BY_THE_POWER_VESTED_IN_ME_BY_THE                                       = 10846,  -- By the power vested in me by the Republic of Bastok, I hereby pronounce you husband and wife.
        YOU_ARE_ALL_NOW_OFFICIALLY_PERMITTED_TO_EAT                            = 10847,  -- You are all now officially permitted to eat, drink, sing, and have a joyous night!
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_DO_NOTHING_REQUEST                              = 10848,  -- What would you like to do? Nothing. Request a marriage certificate. Learn about marriage certificates. Learn about wedding ceremonies. Learn about ceremonial items.
        HAVE_A_MARRIAGE_CERTIFICATE_ISSUED_YES_NO                              = 10849,  -- Have a marriage certificate issued? Yes. No.
        IT_APPEARS_YOUR_BETTER_HALF_HAS_MADE_A                                 = 10850,  -- It appears your better half has made a change. Please restart the process.
        AN_ASSORTMENT_OF_CELEBRATORY_GOODS_IS_AVAILABLE_FOR                    = 10851,  -- An assortment of celebratory goods is available for purchase.
        AN_ASSORTMENT_OF_WEDDING_ATTIRE_AND_WEDDING_RINGS                      = 10852,  -- An assortment of wedding attire and wedding rings are available for purchase.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_BUY_SET_GIL_GIL_NOTHING                                  = 10853,  -- What will you buy? [Wedding dress/Benedight] set: # gil. %: # gil. Nothing.
        THIS_SET_INCLUDES_A_BENEDIGHT_COAT_AND_A                               = 10854,  -- This set includes a benedight coat and a pair of benedight hose. Price: # gil.
        THIS_SET_INCLUDES_A_BRIDAL_CORSAGE_A_WEDDING                           = 10855,  -- This set includes a bridal corsage, a wedding dress, a pair of wedding hose, and a pair of wedding boots. Price: # gil.
        CONFIRM_PURCHASE_CURRENT_GIL_YES_CANCEL                                = 10856,  -- Confirm purchase? (Current gil: #) Yes. Cancel.
        ENDCODE                                                                = 10857,  -- endcode:#
        HM_BUSINESS_WITH_THE_PRESIDENT_YE_SAY                                  = 10858,  -- Hm? Business with the president, ye say?
        IRON_EATER_WHAT_S_THE_DISTURBANCE_HERE                                 = 10859,  -- Iron Eater! What's the disturbance here?
        SIR_LUCIUS_THIS_ADVENTURER_HERE_S_BROUGHT_A                            = 10860,  -- Sir Lucius. This adventurer here's brought a curious document.
        LET_ME_SEE_THAT                                                        = 10861,  -- Let me see that.
        THE_TWO_HEADED_SERPENT_THIS_IS_THE_SEAL                                = 10862,  -- The two-headed serpent...? This is the seal of the Empire of Aht Urhgan.
        COME_WITH_ME_AT_ONCE                                                   = 10863,  -- Come with me at once.
        THAT_WILL_DO                                                           = 10864,  -- ...That will do.
        HOW_DO_YOU_READ_THIS_MATTER_LUCIUS                                     = 10865,  -- How do you read this matter, Lucius?
        THIS_YOUNG_EMPRESS_IS_EITHER_A_FOOL_OR                                 = 10866,  -- This young Empress is either a fool, or she takes us for one. I say she's plotting something.
        ONE_THING_IS_CLEAR_THIS_COLOSSUS_HAS_THE                               = 10867,  -- One thing is clear. This colossus has the power to bring down an airship as easily as a musketeer would fell a pigeon.
        WE_MAY_HAVE_ESCAPED_WITHOUT_CASUALTIES_ONCE_BUT                        = 10868,  -- We may have escaped without casualties once, but there is no guarantee we would be so fortunate a second time.
        BASTOK_DECLINES_THE_EMPIRE_S_REQUEST_TAKE_YOUR                         = 10869,  -- Bastok declines the Empire's request. Take your document and be off with you.
        MISTER_PRESIDENT                                                       = 10870,  -- Mister President!
        YOU_SENT_ME_TO_THE_EMPIRE_TO_OBSERVE                                   = 10871,  -- You sent me to the Empire to observe Nashmeira's coronation. Now hear me when I say that I saw no deception in her eyes.
        I_SAW_ONE_PURE_OF_HEART_ONE_WHO                                        = 10872,  -- I saw one pure of heart. One who, despite her tender years, is possessed of the strength and conviction to unite a nation.
        ID_10873                                                               = 10873,  -- ...
        A_LEADER_BELOVED_AND_TRUSTED_BY_HER_PEOPLE                             = 10874,  -- A leader beloved and trusted by her people. A leader who now earnestly seeks our aid.
        IF_WE_REFUSE_WOULD_WE_NOT_RISK_ALIENATING                              = 10875,  -- If we refuse, would we not risk alienating one who might prove to be a steadfast ally?
        ID_10876                                                               = 10876,  -- ...
        YOUR_WORDS_RING_TRUE_VOLKER                                            = 10877,  -- Your words ring true, Volker.
        AND_YET_I_CANNOT_AGREE_AS_PRESIDENT_I                                  = 10878,  -- And yet I cannot agree. As President, I will not take a course of action that would place my citizens in harm's way.
        YOUR_EXCELLENCY                                                        = 10879,  -- ...Your Excellency.
        LUCIUS                                                                 = 10880,  -- Lucius?
        I_CAN_SCARCE_BELIEVE_WHAT_I_AM_SAYING                                  = 10881,  -- I can scarce believe what I am saying, but...if Captain Volker is so convinced of the Empire's good faith, perhaps we should reconsider.
        TWO_OF_MY_MOST_TRUSTED_ADVISORS_NOW_TELL                               = 10882,  -- Two of my most trusted advisors now tell me to blindly accept this Empress's words. What say you, %?
        CAN_NASHMEIRA_BE_TRUSTED_I_SWEAR_ON_MY                                 = 10883,  -- Can Nashmeira be trusted? I swear on my life. On second thought...
        HMPH_AND_WHAT_WOULD_A_RUN_OF_THE                                       = 10884,  -- Hmph...and what would a run-of-the-mill adventurer like you know?
        HMPH_I_STAND_IN_THE_COMPANY_OF_RECKLESS                                = 10885,  -- Hmph. I stand in the company of reckless fools...
        HMPH_I_STAND_IN_THE_COMPANY_OF_RECKLESS_2                              = 10886,  -- Hmph. I stand in the company of reckless fools...
        WHAT_ARE_YOU_THINKING                                                  = 10887,  -- What are you thinking, %!?
        VERY_WELL_YOU_HAVE_MY_PERMISSION                                       = 10888,  -- ...Very well. You have my permission.
        VOLKER_THE_MOMENT_ANYTHING_ANYTHING_I_SAY_GOES                         = 10889,  -- Volker. The moment anything--anything, I say--goes awry, you will take responsibility.
        MISTER_PRESIDENT_SIR                                                   = 10890,  -- Mister President, sir!
        MY_FRIENDS_I_AM_PLEASED_TO_SEE_YOUR                                    = 10891,  -- My friends. I am pleased to see your safe return.
        NEVER_WOULD_I_HAVE_SUSPECTED_THAT_CAPTAIN_KLARA                        = 10892,  -- Never would I have suspected that Captain Klara was possessed by one of those foul creatures...
        AND_YET_REFLECTING_BACK_ON_THE_PAST_MONTHS                             = 10893,  -- And yet, reflecting back on the past months, it explains much.
        IN_MY_IGNORANCE_I_THOUGHT_IT_MERELY_THE                                = 10894,  -- In my ignorance, I thought it merely the travails of war that weighed on her mind. To think that she was waging an even fiercer battle all this time. A battle for her very soul...
        THE_KNOWLEDGE_THAT_SHE_MAY_LOSE_HERSELF_COMPLETELY                     = 10895,  -- The knowledge that she may lose herself completely, that at any moment she might turn her blade against her beloved comrades... It must have been harrowing, indeed.
        THIS_I_KNOW_KLARA_IS_FORTUNATE_INDEED_TO                               = 10896,  -- This I know: Klara is fortunate indeed to have friends such as you. Were it not for your efforts, there is little doubt we would have lost her long ago.
        ON_BEHALF_OF_THE_ENTIRE_REPUBLIC_YOU_HAVE                              = 10897,  -- On behalf of the entire republic, you have my gratitude.
        AND_YET_OUR_BATTLE_IS_FAR_FROM_OVER                                    = 10898,  -- And yet, our battle is far from over.
        THE_LATEST_REPORT_HAS_JUST_COME_IN_FROM                                = 10899,  -- The latest report has just come in from the front lines. Thanks to the efforts of the Allied infiltration unit, we've finally secured a direct line of attack against the enemy stronghold.
        THE_ALLIED_FORCES_WILL_MOVE_AGAINST_CASTLE_ZVAHL                       = 10900,  -- The Allied Forces will move against Castle Zvahl with the full brunt of its strength. I will personally lead the Republican Army in support of this offensive.
        I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_MARCH_WITH_ME_UNDER                                   = 10901,  -- I would have you march with me. Under normal circumstances, you'd have earned yourselves a rest for your efforts, but I'm afraid that is a luxury we cannot afford.
        MISTER_PRESIDENT_DOES_THIS_MEAN                                        = 10902,  -- Mister President...does this mean--?
        BY_PRESIDENTIAL_DECREE_THE_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEERS_ARE_HEREBY               = 10903,  -- By presidential decree, the Mythril Musketeers are hereby reinstated in full.
        ZEID_UNTIL_SUCH_TIME_AS_CAPTAIN_KLARA_IS                               = 10904,  -- Zeid. Until such time as Captain Klara is fit to return to duty, I would have you serve as acting captain in her stead.
        CLEARLY_THE_BONDS_YOU_SHARE_ARE_AS_STRONG                              = 10905,  -- Clearly, the bonds you share are as strong--nay, stronger--than the metal from which you take your name. Let these bonds of friendship be your strength, and even the darkest shadow will prove no match for you.
        YES_SIR_4                                                              = 10906,  -- Yes, sir!
        AND_YOU                                                                = 10907,  -- And you, %...
        YOU_HAIL_FROM_A_DISTANT_REALM_THIS_I                                   = 10908,  -- You hail from a distant realm, this I know. Despite this, you have made one sacrifice after the next in our Republic's name.
        IT_WOULD_BE_NO_EXAGGERATION_TO_SAY_THAT                                = 10909,  -- It would be no exaggeration to say that without your unflagging efforts, Bastok would not stand as strong as it does today.
        AS_A_TOKEN_OF_MY_GRATITUDE_I_GIVE                                      = 10910,  -- As a token of my gratitude, I give you this.
        FURTHERMORE_FROM_THIS_DAY_FORWARD_YOU_SHALL_BE                         = 10911,  -- Furthermore, from this day forward you shall be a full-fledged member of the Mythril Musketeers. The Republic would have your strength for as long as it stands.
        THREE_CHEERS_FOR_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER                                     = 10912,  -- Three cheers for Mythril Musketeer %!
        THEY_TELL_ME_OUR_GUARDSMAN_GENTLE_TIGER_HAS                            = 10913,  -- They tell me our guardsman Gentle Tiger has dubbed you the Sixth Musketeer. I will do him one better: I hereby bestow upon you the designation of Mythril Musketeer Zero.
        A_WAYFARER_FROM_FAR_OFF_LANDS_YOU_ARE                                  = 10914,  -- A wayfarer from far-off lands you are, and yet serve our nation as loyally as any true Bastoker ever has. Never lose sight of your origins, for it is your unique background that allows you to serve us as no other can.
        ONCE_A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER_FOREVER_A_MYTHRIL_MUSKETEER                   = 10915,  -- Once a Mythril Musketeer, forever a Mythril Musketeer. The Republic is stronger for your presence, %. Promise us that it will always be so.
        SIMPLY_INCREDIBLE_WHY_THE_ZERO_DESIGNATION_IS_AN                       = 10916,  -- Simply incredible... Why, the zero designation is an honor that's been granted to only the most illustrious musketeers in the history of our unit.
        I_MUST_CONFESS_TO_FEELING_A_BIT_OF                                     = 10917,  -- I must confess to feeling a bit of jealousy, %. But just you wait: I fully expect to distinguish myself in the none-too-distant future!
        IT_HAS_BEEN_AND_ALWAYS_WILL_BE_AN                                      = 10918,  -- %. It has been--and always will be--an honor to fight by your side.
        THEY_SAY_THAT_IN_THE_DAYS_OF_THE                                       = 10919,  -- They say that in the days of the Great War, there was a hero of the Republic who distinguished himself/herself] so highly that he/she] was bestowed the title of Mythril Musketeer Zero by President Prien himself.
        HIS_HER_IDENTITY_WAS_NEVER_MADE_PUBLIC_AND                             = 10920,  -- His/Her] identity was never made public, and he/she] remains the only one to this day to receive the honor. What I wouldn't give for the chance to meet such a legend!
        THIS_STUPID_THING_IS_SO_DAMN_COMPLICATED                               = 10921,  -- This stupid thing is so damn complicated.
        COME_ON_NAJI_IT_LL_BE_EASY_NAJI                                        = 10922,  -- Come on, Naji! It'll be easy, Naji! <Grumble> Why did I even agree to this?
        WHO_EXACTLY_VOLUNTEERED_ME_ANYWAY                                      = 10923,  -- Who exactly volunteered me, anyway?
        AND_NOW_I_VE_GOT_SOMEONE_BOTHERING_ME                                  = 10924,  -- And now I've got someone bothering me. What is it?
        BY_ALTANA_SOMEONE_HAS_ACTUALLY_COME_TO_ME                              = 10925,  -- By Altana! Someone has actually come to me about this Trust thing?
        TAKING_THE_BUFFALO_BY_THE_HORNS_ARE_WE                                 = 10926,  -- Taking the buffalo by the horns, are we? I suppose I can find some time in my busy schedule.
        LET_ME_BE_UP_FRONT_WITH_YOU_I                                          = 10927,  -- Let me be up front with you--I've got absolutely no idea how this works. They told me something about trust and friendship, but what exactly is that supposed to mean?
        BUT_IF_IT_WORKS_YOU_LL_BE_ABLE                                         = 10928,  -- But if it works, you'll be able to summon an alter ego of me who'll fight by your side. And let's be honest--who better than me?
        THAT_S_WHAT_I_M_LED_TO_BELIEVE                                         = 10929,  -- That's what I'm led to believe, anyway. Pretty amazing stuff!
        BUT_I_DON_T_KNOW_YOU_FROM_A                                            = 10930,  -- But I don't know you from a crying street urchin, so it probably won't work. Tough luck, kid.
        AND_SINCE_WE_VE_BEEN_THROUGH_SOME_INTERESTING                          = 10931,  -- And since we've been through some interesting times together, it might be crazy enough to work!
        YOU_WERE_SENT_ON_THAT_RECONNAISSANCE_MISSION_TO                        = 10932,  -- You were sent on that reconnaissance mission to San d'Oria and Windurst at the behest of President Karst.
        YOU_KNOW_I_WAS_POSTED_TO_THESE_GATES                                   = 10933,  -- You know I was posted to these gates to keep undesirables out of his hair, but I knew I could count on you, so I let you pass.
        REMEMBER_THAT_TIME_GRANDMA_ASKED_YOU_TO_REFORGE                        = 10934,  -- Remember that time Grandma asked you to reforge my father's sword?
        YOU_D_BETTER_STILL_HAVE_THAT_AXE_I                                     = 10935,  -- You'd better still have that axe I gave you! Sure got me through some tough times over the years, and I'd sure hate to hear that it's shoved haphazardly in the back of your Mog Locker.
        THAT_WHOLE_DEBACLE_WITH_THE_KING_OF_HEARTS                             = 10936,  -- That whole debacle with the King of Hearts and I in Aht Urhgan sure was a time to remember. You're lucky we managed to pull your ass out of the fire!
        YOU_REALLY_GAVE_ME_WHAT_FOR_AT_THAT                                    = 10937,  -- You really gave me what for at that chocobo race, too. It's taken me a while to forgive you!
        BUT_NAJI_THAT_WAS_AGES_AGO_BAH_NEXT                                    = 10938,  -- But, Naji, that was ages ago! Bah! Next time you won't be so lucky!
        AH_MEMORIES_IF_I_WERE_A_WEAKER_MAN                                     = 10939,  -- Ah, memories. If I were a weaker man, it might even bring me to tears.
        BUT_THIS_WHOLE_TRUST_MAGIC_ORDEAL_MEMORIES_ALONE                       = 10940,  -- But this whole Trust magic ordeal...memories alone don't make strong bonds! You're going to need a bit more than that!
        IRON_EATER_ALWAYS_CALLED_ME_DUMB_AS_A                                  = 10941,  -- Iron Eater always called me dumb as a tree stump and simple as a wooden spear, but I'll have you know I am both complex and intricate!
        SO_DON_T_BLAME_ME_IF_THIS_FAILS                                        = 10942,  -- So don't blame me if this fails. It's all on your head.
        NOW_CONCENTRATE_MY_COMPATRIOT_FOCUS_ON_YOUR_FEELINGS                   = 10943,  -- Now, concentrate, my compatriot! Focus on your feelings of trust and friendship!
        IF_YOU_WON_T_BELIEVE_IN_ME_THEN                                        = 10944,  -- If you won't believe in me, then believe in the fact that I believe in you! Wait, what did I just say?
        THIS_IS_ALL_THAT_IT_TOOK_THAT_IDIOT                                    = 10945,  -- This is all that it took? That idiot Clarion Star gave such a long explanation of sorts that I was ready to stand here for hours and hours!
        BUT_I_LL_BE_DAMNED_IF_THIS_DOESN                                       = 10946,  -- But I'll be damned if this doesn't feel good. Let's try it out!
        HEY_YOU_LITTLE_GET_BACK_HERE                                           = 10947,  -- Hey, you little--get back here!!!
        PHEW_THAT_COULD_HAVE_ENDED_VERY_BADLY_AT                               = 10948,  -- Phew! That could have ended very badly. At least I can control the thing.
        HA_NOW_I_CAN_GUARD_TWO_DOORS_AT                                        = 10949,  -- Ha! Now I can guard two doors at the same time! Wait...why am I getting excited about that?
        I_AM_THE_QUINTESSENTIAL_WARRIOR_NUMBER_FIVE_IN                         = 10950,  -- I am the quintessential warrior, number five in the Mythril Musketeer hierarchy, and if I ever catch you referring to me as a doorman, I'll bite your head off!
        UGGGH_THIS_DOORMAN_THING_HITS_A_LITTLE_TOO                             = 10951,  -- Ugggh...this doorman thing hits a little too close to home.
