        GIVE_IT_A_SHAKE_OUTSIDE_OF_TOWN_MAYBE                                  = 10957,  -- Give it a shake outside of town. Maybe North or South Gustaberg, for instance. I'm sure you'll be more than pleased with the result.
        AND_FAR_BE_IT_FROM_ME_TO_CONFESS                                       = 10958,  -- And far be it from me to confess my weakness...but I'm a bit curious as to whether it will actually work. Come back to me once you've tried it out.
        TELL_ME_EVERY_LAST_DETAIL_DID_MY_ALTER                                 = 10959,  -- Tell me every last detail! Did my alter ego do the real me justice?
        HOW_DID_IT_GO_COULDN_T_BE_HAPPIER                                      = 10960,  -- How did it go? Couldn't be happier. Well...I'm not too impressed.
        CAN_T_SAY_THAT_I_M_SURPRISED_WHEN                                      = 10961,  -- Can't say that I'm surprised. When you're working with a man like me, of course you'll get great results. Now you know why Iron Eater chose who he did!
        NOT_IMPRESSED_STOP_BLATHERING_ON_LIKE_A_BABY                           = 10962,  -- Not impressed? Stop blathering on like a baby!
        HOW_COULDN_T_YOU_BE_IMPRESSED_BY_SOMEONE                               = 10963,  -- How couldn't you be impressed by someone so complex and intricate?
        BE_THAT_AS_IT_MAY_IF_YOU_NEED                                          = 10964,  -- Be that as it may, if you need to learn more about Trust, just go back and ask Clarion Star. He seems to know a lot about this stuff.
        HE_KEPT_MUTTERING_SOMETHING_ABOUT_LATENT_POTENTIAL_AND                 = 10965,  -- He kept muttering something about latent potential and ongoing research or what-have-you. I wasn't really paying attention.
        BUT_WHAT_I_DID_FIND_INTERESTING_WAS_THAT                               = 10966,  -- But what I did find interesting was that there are also people in other nations with their gaze trained on this program.
        IF_THE_WHOLE_PROCESS_CONFOUNDS_ME_THEN_IT                              = 10967,  -- If the whole process confounds me, then it's no surprise that there are people out there trying to figure out just how it works.
        BUT_YOU_DON_T_NEED_TO_CROSS_THE                                        = 10968,  -- But you don't need to cross the border to find out more. Some other people here in Bastok are participating, like...Ayame.
        SHE_S_NUMBER_FOUR_HERE_IN_THE_MYTHRIL                                  = 10969,  -- She's number four here in the Mythril Musketeers, and I doubt she'd let just any old adventurer try out Trust magic with her.
        Y_YOU_WANT_ME_TO_ASK_HER_FOR                                           = 10970,  -- Y-you want me to ask her for you? No, no, I don't think that would be a good idea.
        SHE_KNOWS_YOU_PRETTY_WELL_BY_NOW_JUST                                  = 10971,  -- She knows you pretty well by now. Just give her a quick kick for me when you go see her, hmm?
        THERE_S_SOMETHING_ELSE_I_MUST_GIVE_YOU                                 = 10972,  -- There's something else I must give you: this %. Well, there's nothing more you need from me here.
        YOU_VE_GOT_WHAT_YOU_CAME_FOR_JUST                                      = 10973,  -- You've got what you came for. Just make sure to treat my alter ego well, or I'll have to hunt you down--and you won't be happy when I find you!
        IT_IS_A_PLEASURE_TO_OH_YOU_HAVE                                        = 10974,  -- It is a pleasure to... Oh? You have %?
        I_AM_ASSISTING_THE_JEUNO_INSTITUTE_OF_MAGICAL                          = 10975,  -- I am assisting the Jeuno Institute of Magical Studies in gathering data on this new Trust magic.
        ONE_OF_MY_DUTIES_AS_A_RANKING_MEMBER                                   = 10976,  -- One of my duties as a ranking member of the Mythril Musketeers is to ensure that we are ready for any eventuality--and it is my firm belief that this new discovery may serve us well.
        IT_IS_MY_FERVENT_HOPE_THAT_IT_WILL                                     = 10977,  -- It is my fervent hope that it will aid us in our struggles against the Beastman Confederate. If not, perhaps it can at least be used to assist with some of our more menial tasks.
        IF_POSSIBLE_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO_ENLIST_YOUR                                = 10978,  -- If possible, I would like to enlist your aid in this endeavor.
        BUT_UNFORTUNATELY_IT_SEEMS_THIS_MAGIC_WOULD_REQUIRE                    = 10979,  -- But unfortunately, it seems this magic would require a bond between us, a bond we do not yet share.
        THERE_ARE_OTHER_THINGS_YOU_MUST_TAKE_CARE                              = 10980,  -- There are other things you must take care of first. I wish you the best in your efforts to protect [Bastok/your homeland].
        THE_VERY_FACT_THAT_YOU_HAVE_CHOSEN_TO                                  = 10981,  -- The very fact that you have chosen to visit me this day can only mean one thing. You wish to see whether you can call forth my alter ego.
        ATTEMPT_THE_RITUAL_WITH_AYAME_LET_S_GIVE                               = 10982,  -- Attempt the ritual with Ayame? Let's give this a shot. Not at the moment.
        I_WOULD_URGE_YOU_TO_RECONSIDER_THIS_CITY                               = 10983,  -- I would urge you to reconsider. This city requires more strength and resolve; the last thing it needs is more Najis.
        REMEMBER_THAT_THIS_MAGIC_DRAWS_ON_THE_POWER                            = 10984,  -- Remember that this magic draws on the power of deeply personal bonds. Bonds which can both steady the heart and set it to racing.
        LET_US_THINK_BACK_ONCE_MORE_TO_ALL                                     = 10985,  -- Let us think back once more to all that has transpired between us.
        YOU_RESCUED_ME_FROM_THE_TERRIFYING_CLUTCHES_OF                         = 10986,  -- You rescued me from the terrifying clutches of a dragon in Waughroon Shrine.
        MY_ALTER_EGO_IS_BUT_A_REFLECTION_OF                                    = 10987,  -- My alter ego is but a reflection of myself. Should you succeed in calling out to her, she will surely remember your deeds.
        ID_10988                                                               = 10988,  -- [You aided me when Volker chose to give up his position as the head of our troupe./You also aided me when Volker chose to give up his position as the head of our troupe.]
        THE_ONLY_REASON_THE_MUSKETEERS_WERE_ABLE_TO                            = 10989,  -- The only reason the Musketeers were able to reclaim their former glory was due to your valiant efforts during the battle between Zeid and our leader.
        YOU_HELPED_ME_DURING_THAT_INCIDENT_WITH_VIRESEFILANT                   = 10990,  -- [I remember now./And there's more.] You [/also ]helped me during that incident with Viresefilant when I made one of my journeys to Norg.
        OUR_EFFORTS_IN_THAT_CASE_BORE_CERTAIN_FRUIT                            = 10991,  -- Our efforts in that case bore certain fruit. We were able to confirm the details of an agreement vital to Bastokan interests.
        WOULD_ONLY_THAT_THE_DARK_UNDERBELLY_OF_BASTOK                          = 10992,  -- Would only that the dark underbelly of Bastok had not been exposed to you in the process... One day I hope to bring it to its rightful conclusion.
        OH_I_WOULD_BE_LOATH_TO_FORGET_MY                                       = 10993,  -- Oh, [/and ]I would be loath to forget my younger sister, Kaede. My father mentioned that it was your help that guided my sister down her path.
        SOMETIMES_I_TALK_WITH_HER_ABOUT_MY_MOTHER                              = 10994,  -- Sometimes I talk with her about my mother...and somehow, your name always comes up.
        NAJI_TOLD_ME_OF_YOUR_MOMENTOUS_EXPLOITS_OVER                           = 10995,  -- [You know,/And what's more,] Naji told me of your momentous exploits over in Aht Urhgan.
        I_M_QUITE_SURE_HIS_ROLE_WAS_LESS                                       = 10996,  -- I'm quite sure his role was less significant than he made it out to be, and we truly have you to thank for how things turned out.
        MY_HEART_SKIPPED_A_BEAT_WHEN_I_HEARD                                   = 10997,  -- My heart skipped a beat when I heard that the airship came tumbling down like a boulder rolled off a cliff.
        WHO_COULD_FORGET_WHEN_YOU_VANQUISHED_HUU_XALMO                         = 10998,  -- Who could forget when you vanquished Huu Xalmo the Savage, displaying your true prowess as one of the finest monks in the land?
        YOU_HAVE_TAKEN_THE_PATH_MY_PREDECESSOR_CORNELIA                        = 10999,  -- You have taken the path my predecessor Cornelia took and made it your own. As a member of the Mythril Musketeers, I understand like no other what that decision means.
        HOW_COULD_I_FORGET_THAT_YOU_BEAT_INFINITY                              = 11000,  -- How could I forget that you beat Infinity XIII!?
        YOU_REMEMBER_DURING_THE_CHOCOBO_RACES_TO_THINK                         = 11001,  -- You remember--during the chocobo races. To think that I lost after all the effort I put into my chocobo's care. But it was a battle well-fought, and one that I thoroughly enjoyed.
        FLASHING_DANCE_OF_BLADES_IN_DELKFUTT_S_TOWER                           = 11002,  -- [The/Further, the] flashing dance of blades in Delkfutt's Tower taught me more about swordsmanship than I ever thought possible. One dream of mine is that we may sometime spar again as we did that day.
        WHO_ELSE_COULD_HAVE_FELLED_SO_MANY_IN                                  = 11003,  -- Who else could have felled so many in such a short period of time? There was a spark in your eyes and a spring in your step that few can hope to replicate.
        WHAT_CALLED_YOU_TO_PARTICIPATE_IN_THIS_GRAND                           = 11004,  -- [So let me ask,/Since you are here,] what called you to participate in this grand experiment?
        YOU_NEED_NOT_RESPOND_I_SPOKE_FOR_YOUR                                  = 11005,  -- You need not respond. I spoke for your benefit, not my own.
