        ID_11379                                                               = 11379,  -- @@
        HOW_HOW_DID_I_NOT_PLACE_FIRST_IF                                       = 11380,  -- How!? How did I not place first? If there's one thing I know, it's how to get my outfit perfect...
        AND_NOW_I_VE_GOT_TO_TRACK_DOWN                                         = 11381,  -- And now I've got to track down a Goblin...ugh.
        HANG_ON_MAYBE_THAT_S_THE_KEY_MAYBE                                     = 11382,  -- Hang on... Maybe that's the key. Maybe I should have gone dressed in all black. <Grumble, grumble>
        UGH_THOSE_THREE_FIENDS_ARE_SNEAKIER_THAN_THEY                          = 11383,  -- Ugh...those three fiends are sneakier than they look. I lost sight of them for one second and completely lost the trail.
        I_DID_SEE_AN_EGGSHELL_LYING_ON_THE                                     = 11384,  -- I did see an eggshell lying on the ground, though, and figured it may have been the one Raebrimm gave them...
        BUT_IT_WAS_JUST_AN_ORDINARY_EGGSHELL                                   = 11385,  -- But it was just an ordinary eggshell.
        GREAT_WHAT_AM_I_SUPPOSED_TO_TELL_IRON                                  = 11386,  -- Great. What am I supposed to tell Iron Eater?
        YOU_NEEDN_T_WORRY_I_TENDED_TO_THE                                      = 11387,  -- You needn't worry. I tended to the wounds of those injured in the mines.
        AS_A_MUSKETEER_I_M_WELL_TRAINED_IN                                     = 11388,  -- As a musketeer, I'm well-trained in the art of healing. Plus, I've had more than my fair share of injuries over the years, which has given me plenty of practice in the field.
        I_HEARD_FROM_LADY_CORNELIA_AND_THE_PEOPLE                              = 11389,  -- I heard from Lady Cornelia and the people who saw the Quadav. It seems the Quadav were searching for something.
        AT_ANY_RATE_I_M_GLAD_NO_REAL                                           = 11390,  -- At any rate, I'm glad no real harm came to the Zeruhn Mines or the people working them.
        AH_IT_S_YOU_DO_YOU_HAVE_BUSINESS                                       = 11391,  -- Ah, it's you. Do you have business in the President's Office?
        YES_AS_A_MATTER_OF_FACT_HE_SHE                                         = 11392,  -- Yes, as a matter of fact, he/she] does.
        HE_SHE_IS_HERE_ABOUT_THE_QUADAV_ATTACK                                 = 11393,  -- He/She] is here about the Quadav attack on the Zeruhn Mines led by Do'Bho Venomtail.
        SURELY_YOU_KNOW_OF_MY_FATHER_S_DECISION                                = 11394,  -- Surely you know of my father's decision, Iron Eater...
        YOU_SHOULD_ASK_HIM_YOURSELF_MY_LADY                                    = 11395,  -- You should ask him yourself, my lady.
        I_ALREADY_TRIED_HE_JUST_GOT_ANGRY_AND                                  = 11396,  -- I already tried. He just got angry and told me to go to my room.
        DO_YOU_KNOW_SOMETHING_WERE_YOU_SUMMONED_TO                             = 11397,  -- Do you know something, %? Were you summoned to the meeting?
        BUT_YOU_WERE_THE_ONE_WHO_DEFEATED_DO                                   = 11398,  -- But you were the one who defeated Do'Bho Venomtail! It's not fair to leave you out of this!
        YES_I_ALSO_BELIEVE_THAT_HAS_A_RIGHT                                    = 11399,  -- Yes, I also believe that % has a right to know the truth.
        IRON_EATER_WOULD_YOU_MIND_EXPLAINING_IT_TO                             = 11400,  -- Iron Eater, would you mind explaining it to him/her]?
        FIRST_OF_ALL_OUR_INVESTIGATION_AT_THE_ZERUHN                           = 11401,  -- First of all, our investigation at the Zeruhn Mines went exactly as we expected. The Quadav forces came down the river from the Palborough Mines.
        WITNESSES_AT_THE_SCENE_SAY_THAT_THE_QUADAV                             = 11402,  -- Witnesses at the scene say that the Quadav were chasing something.
        MEANWHILE_THREE_BEASTMEN_LED_BY_A_GOBLIN_CLAD                          = 11403,  -- Meanwhile, three beastmen led by a Goblin clad in black were seen racing toward the Bastok Mines.
        WHAT_A_BLACK_CLAD_GOBLIN_SURELY_IT_MUST                                = 11404,  -- What!? A black-clad Goblin? Surely, it must've been...
        WHO_WAS_IT_THE_GLOOM_PHANTOM_THE_DESTINY                               = 11405,  -- Who was it? The Gloom Phantom. The Destiny Destroyers. Zeid.
        YES_THAT_S_THE_ONE_YOU_RE_ABSOLUTELY                                   = 11406,  -- Yes, that's the one! You're absolutely right!
        YES_THAT_S_THEM_THE_GROUP_CONSISTING_OF                                = 11407,  -- Yes, that's them! The group consisting of the Gloom Phantom and his friends!
        HUH_SURE_HE_WEARS_BLACK_BUT_I_DON                                      = 11408,  -- Huh!? Sure, he wears black, but I don't think it was him.
        NO_I_M_TALKING_ABOUT_THE_GLOOM_PHANTOM                                 = 11409,  -- No, I'm talking about the Gloom Phantom.
        YES_WE_WERE_THINKING_THE_SAME_THING_SO                                 = 11410,  -- Yes, we were thinking the same thing, so we talked to Raebrimm, who was previously a target of theirs.
        HOWEVER_WE_DID_NOT_REALLY_LEARN_ANYTHING_NEW                           = 11411,  -- However, we did not really learn anything new. It appears that Raebrimm is not involved.
        YES_THAT_MAKES_SENSE_THE_DESTINY_DESTROYERS_WERE                       = 11412,  -- Yes, that makes sense... The Destiny Destroyers were satisfied once they got that eggshell, right?
        ALTHOUGH_THEIR_REAL_OBJECTIVE_WAS_THE_EGG_AND                          = 11413,  -- Although, their real objective was the egg, and we're still not sure about the reason why.
        DID_YOU_FIND_OUT_ANYTHING                                              = 11414,  -- Did you find out anything, %?
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_TALK_ABOUT_THE_YAGUDO_AND                                = 11415,  -- What will you talk about? The Yagudo and Orc conspiracy. The Destiny Destroyers. The World Eater Egg.
        WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_SAY_THE_YAGUDO_WERE                                    = 11416,  -- What's that you say? The Yagudo were searching for the egg in Windurst!?
        AND_AN_ORCISH_UNIT_WAS_DISPATCHED_TO_SAN                               = 11417,  -- And an Orcish unit was dispatched to San d'Oria...
        SO_THESE_BEASTMEN_ARE_ALL_TRYING_TO_STEAL                              = 11418,  -- So these beastmen are all trying to steal the egg for themselves. That means the Quadav probably are as well...
        YOU_RE_TALKING_ABOUT_THAT_TRIO_THAT_SHOWED                             = 11419,  -- You're talking about that trio that showed up where the egg was?
        AND_THEY_WORKED_TOGETHER_ALONGSIDE_THE_ORCS_IN                         = 11420,  -- And they worked together alongside the Orcs in the Northlands to break open the egg.
        SO_IF_THEY_VE_SHOWN_UP_HERE_THEN                                       = 11421,  -- So, if they've shown up here, then that means... Wait, could the egg be somewhere near Bastok?
        IF_SO_THEN_THAT_MIGHT_MEAN_THEY_RE                                     = 11422,  -- If so, then that might mean they're here to break open this egg for themselves.
        SOME_LEGENDARY_EGG_THAT_GIVES_UNTOLD_POWER_IF                          = 11423,  -- Some legendary egg that gives untold power if broken open? I find it all rather hard to believe.
        FORTUNATELY_IF_WHAT_YOU_SAY_IS_TRUE_THEN                               = 11424,  -- Fortunately, if what you say is true, then that power is not so easily obtained.
        THAT_ORC_WAS_DESTROYED_WHEN_HE_BROKE_OPEN                              = 11425,  -- That Orc was destroyed when he broke open the egg. I suppose the power was too much for him to bear.
        WHAT_IF_SOMEONE_CAPABLE_OF_WIELDING_THAT_POWER                         = 11426,  -- What if someone capable of wielding that power were to appear? The mere thought of such a thing terrifies me.
        WE_MUST_INFORM_SIR_LUCIUS_ABOUT_THIS_MATTER                            = 11427,  -- We must inform Sir Lucius about this matter immediately.
        I_MUST_TELL_MY_FATHER_ABOUT_THIS_WORLD                                 = 11428,  -- I must tell my father about this World Eater Egg right away. The Quadav can wait.
        NO_MY_LADY_LIKE_THE_OTHER_BEASTMEN_THE                                 = 11429,  -- No, my lady. Like the other beastmen, the Quadav are also hoping to harness the egg's power.
        IN_FACT_THEY_MAY_HAVE_ALREADY_OBTAINED_THAT                            = 11430,  -- In fact, they may have already obtained that power.
        SO_YOU_MEAN_THEY_PURPOSELY_SHOWED_UP_AT                                = 11431,  -- So you mean they purposely showed up at the Zeruhn Mines in order to provoke us? That they are hoping to start a war?
        FIRST_THEY_LEAD_THE_REPUBLICAN_MILITARY_TO_THE                         = 11432,  -- First, they lead the Republican military to the Palborough Mines, where they can use the egg's overwhelming power...
        WAIT_JUST_A_MOMENT_SIR_VOLKER_IRON_EATER                               = 11433,  -- Wait just a moment, Sir Volker, Iron Eater...
        DO_YOU_MEAN_TO_SAY_THAT_MY_FATHER                                      = 11434,  -- Do you mean to say that my father intends to start a war?
        UM                                                                     = 11435,  -- Um...
        I_KNOW_THAT_THE_QUADAV_ARE_OUR_SWORN                                   = 11436,  -- I know that the Quadav are our sworn enemy. However, we must remain calm if we are to avoid needless bloodshed.
        NATURALLY_THERE_ARE_MANY_WHO_SHARE_YOUR_OPINION                        = 11437,  -- Naturally, there are many who share your opinion, my lady. Whether they can sway the opinion of the Senate, however...
        WE_HAVE_TO_AT_LEAST_TRY_ONCE_WE                                        = 11438,  -- We have to at least try! Once we set down the path to war, there's no turning back!
        THEY_SAY_VICTORY_FAVORS_THOSE_WHO_MOVE_FIRST                           = 11439,  -- They say victory favors those who move first.
        I_REALIZE_I_MAY_BE_A_YOUNG_GIRL                                        = 11440,  -- I realize I may be a young girl who knows little of the ways of the world...
        HOWEVER_THAT_IS_ALSO_WHY_I_CAN_SAY                                     = 11441,  -- However, that is also why I can say what needs to be said. There are things that people must know if we are to go to war.
        WHAT_IF_YOU_WERE_TO_ENLIST_S_SERVICES                                  = 11442,  -- What if you were to enlist %'s services, my lady?
        YES_THAT_IS_AN_EXCELLENT_IDEA                                          = 11443,  -- Yes, that is an excellent idea.
        PLEASE_CAN_YOU_GO_INVESTIGATE_THE_PALBOROUGH_MINES                     = 11444,  -- Please, %! Can you go investigate the Palborough Mines for us?
        WE_NEED_TO_KNOW_IF_THE_QUADAV_HAVE                                     = 11445,  -- We need to know if the Quadav have acquired the World Eater Egg or the power it holds within. And if not, we need to know what their plans are.
        YOU_MUST_HELP_US_DECIDE_WHETHER_BASTOK_NEEDS                           = 11446,  -- You must help us decide whether Bastok needs to engage the Quadav in all-out war.
        WILL_YOU_AGREE_TO_THE_REQUEST_YES_I                                    = 11447,  -- Will you agree to the request? Yes, I'll do it. Sorry, I can't help you.
        YOU_HAVE_THE_GRATITUDE_OF_OUR_ENTIRE_NATION                            = 11448,  -- You have the gratitude of our entire nation. I shall go and speak to my father.
        ADDITIONALLY_I_SHALL_SPEAK_TO_EVERYONE_INVOLVED_WITH                   = 11449,  -- Additionally, I shall speak to everyone involved with this incident to see if we are missing anything.
        UNTIL_WE_MEET_AGAIN                                                    = 11450,  -- Until we meet again!
        YOU_MUST_HELP_US_THIS_MATTER_CONCERNS_YOU                              = 11451,  -- You must help us! This matter concerns you too! We can't let ourselves go blindly into war!
        IF_THE_SENATE_DECIDES_TO_GO_TO_WAR                                     = 11452,  -- If the Senate decides to go to war, there is little that can be done. However, I do wish to avoid any unnecessary harm to the republic.
        I_WISH_YOU_LUCK                                                        = 11453,  -- I wish you luck, %.
        HEAD_TO_THE_PALBOROUGH_MINES_AND_FIND_OUT                              = 11454,  -- Head to the Palborough Mines and find out whether the Quadav have obtained the World Eater Egg or not. We also need you to find out what they're up to.
        PLEASE_CARRY_OUT_OUR_LADY_S_REQUEST_AS                                 = 11455,  -- Please carry out our lady's request as quickly as you are able. There might not be much time remaining.
        AH_YOU_RE_BACK_AT_LAST_THE_GOOD                                        = 11456,  -- Ah, you're back at last. The good lady has eagerly awaited your return.
        I_MOST_DEFINITELY_HAVE                                                 = 11457,  -- I most definitely have!
        YOU_MUST_TELL_US_ABOUT_THE_QUADAV_AT                                   = 11458,  -- You must tell us about the Quadav at once! Before it's too late!
        I_KNEW_IT_THE_QUADAV_THAT_APPEARED_AT                                  = 11459,  -- I knew it! The Quadav that appeared at the Zeruhn Mines weren't part of some assassination squad!
        SO_JUST_AS_WE_THOUGHT_THEY_WERE_CHASING                                = 11460,  -- So just as we thought, they were chasing after the Destiny Destroyers, yes?
        WHEN_THEY_BROKE_OPEN_THE_WORLD_EATER_EGG                               = 11461,  -- When they broke open the World Eater Egg, the Quadav's eggs were consumed...
        IT_S_ONLY_NATURAL_THAT_THEY_D_BE                                       = 11462,  -- It's only natural that they'd be out for blood.
        CAN_WE_REALLY_BE_SURE_THAT_THE_QUADAV                                  = 11463,  -- Can we really be sure that the Quadav weren't after the power contained within the World Eater Egg for themselves?
        I_THINK_SO_BESIDES_IF_THEY_WERE_TRULY                                  = 11464,  -- I think so. Besides, if they were truly planning to use its power, I think they would've used the scorpion to their advantage too.
        BUT_THE_QUADAV_WERE_ALSO_TRYING_TO_KILL                                = 11465,  -- But the Quadav were also trying to kill the scorpion.
        THAT_MAKES_SENSE_I_THINK_WE_MIGHT_JUST                                 = 11466,  -- That makes sense. I think we might just be able to convince the president...
        THAT_S_EXCELLENT_NEWS_NOW_WE_CAN_FORGET                                = 11467,  -- That's excellent news! Now we can forget about this stupid war with the Quadav!
        HOWEVER_THAT_MAGE_WHO_ABSORBED_THE_POWER_FROM                          = 11468,  -- However, that mage who absorbed the power from the mind-warped scorpion is sure to be a problem.
        HM_YOU_RE_TALKING_ABOUT_THE_TARUTARU_MAGE                              = 11469,  -- Hm!? You're talking about the Tarutaru mage Uran-Mafran! Is he a mage from the Federation of Windurst?
        IF_SO_THEN_BASTOK_S_ENEMY_IS_NOT                                       = 11470,  -- If so, then Bastok's enemy is not the Quadav, but possibly the Federation of Windurst instead.
        IT_S_OKAY_THAT_S_STILL_JUST_CONJECTURE                                 = 11471,  -- It's okay... That's still just conjecture.
        LIKE_WE_DID_WITH_THE_QUADAV_WE_JUST                                    = 11472,  -- Like we did with the Quadav, we just need to find out the truth of the matter.
        YOU_RE_RIGHT_NOW_THEN_WE_NEED_TO                                       = 11473,  -- You're right. Now then, we need to find out more about this mage known as Uran-Mafran.
        I_LL_GET_CAPTAIN_VOLKER_UP_TO_SPEED                                    = 11474,  -- I'll get Captain Volker up to speed on everything that's happened. After that, I want you and him to speak with the president...
        UNDERSTOOD_2                                                           = 11475,  -- Understood!
        ALTHOUGH_BEFORE_I_GO_TO_SPEAK_WITH_VOLKER                              = 11476,  -- Although, before I go to speak with Volker...
        PLEASE_TAKE_THIS_PRESENT_FROM_ME_I_ALWAYS                              = 11477,  -- Please, take this present from me. I always cook whenever I'm worried about something...
        ALSO_THERE_S_SOMETHING_I_MUST_TELL_YOU                                 = 11478,  -- Also, there's something I must tell you.
        YOU_HAVE_MY_UTMOST_GRATITUDE                                           = 11479,  -- You have my utmost gratitude, %.
        THANKS_TO_YOUR_HELP_I_WAS_ABLE_TO                                      = 11480,  -- Thanks to your help, I was able to achieve the outcome I believed to be just.
        HEY_DO_YOU_REMEMBER_WHAT_I_TOLD_YOU                                    = 11481,  -- Hey, do you remember what I told you before?
        THERE_IS_A_LOT_MORE_OF_THIS_COUNTRY                                    = 11482,  -- There is a lot more of this country that I want to learn about. And maybe someday I can become somebody who will represent the people and bring change to Bastok.
        I_HAVE_GROWN_SINCE_THEN_NOW_IT_ISN                                     = 11483,  -- I have grown since then. Now, it isn't just this country that I wish to know more about, but the world itself.
        AND_ONCE_I_DO_I_WANT_TO_HELP                                           = 11484,  -- And once I do, I want to help the people of this country even more. I think I can help my father as well.
        I_FEEL_AS_IF_ALL_THIS_HAS_ENABLED                                      = 11485,  -- I feel as if all this has enabled me to take a first step on that path. That is my duty as the President's daughter...
        AT_ANY_RATE_I_FIRST_NEED_TO_CONVINCE                                   = 11486,  -- At any rate, I first need to convince my father of the cause. Don't worry though, I've got it handled.
        FURTHERMORE_I_THINK_I_UNDERSTAND_WHAT_MY_FATHER                        = 11487,  -- Furthermore, I think I understand what my father means when he says the following...
        I_WON_T_LET_ANYONE_STAND_IN_MY_2                                       = 11488,  -- I won't let anyone stand in my way. He doesn't like people who don't back up their words with action.
        THEREFORE_I_NEED_TO_SHOW_HIM_NOT_JUST                                  = 11489,  -- Therefore, I need to show him, not just tell him. That is my duty as my father's daughter.
        ONE_DAY_I_LL_MAKE_HIM_SEE_IT                                           = 11490,  -- One day, I'll make him see it for himself... He'll see that trusting his daughter is the right thing to do.
        AT_ANY_RATE_I_FIRST_NEED_TO_CONVINCE_2                                 = 11491,  -- At any rate, I first need to convince my father of the cause. Don't worry though, I've got it handled.
        LADY_CORNELIA_LEFT_THIS_WITH_ME_HERE_IT                                = 11492,  -- Lady Cornelia left this with me. Here, it's yours.
        I_ASKED_AYAME_TO_LOOK_INTO_THE_MAGE                                    = 11493,  -- I asked Ayame to look into the mage known as Uran-Mafran. She has connections in Norg, so she's perfect for the task.
        AS_FOR_THE_PRESIDENT_THAT_S_UP_TO                                      = 11494,  -- As for the president, that's up to the good captain and Lady Cornelia... I think it should turn out okay.
        ALTHOUGH_THERE_ARE_STILL_MANY_UNANSWERED_QUESTIONS_ABOUT               = 11495,  -- Although, there are still many unanswered questions about this World Eater Egg. I'm not sure how the Mithril Musketeers should respond.
        THANKS_TO_YOU_WE_HAVE_RECEIVED_VALUABLE_INFORMATION                    = 11496,  -- Thanks to you, we have received valuable information from the Palborough Mines.
        I_HAVE_ASKED_PLENTY_OF_QUESTIONS_BUT_THERE                             = 11497,  -- I have asked plenty of questions, but there is still much I do not understand. In times like these, it is important to proceed with caution.
        HEY_DID_YOU_HEAR_THE_NEWS_AYAME_HAS                                    = 11498,  -- Hey, did you hear the news? Ayame has been given an important mission from Sir Iron Eater.
        YET_I_GET_STUCK_HERE_TENDING_TO_THE                                    = 11499,  -- Yet I get stuck here tending to the wounded. I know it's important work too, but...
        THE_BLACKSMITHS_GUILD_HERE_IS_HUGE_KUPO_THERE                          = 11500,  -- The blacksmiths' guild here is huge, kupo! There's so much to learn!
        HMMM_WAIT_YOU_AREN_T_A_MOOGLE                                          = 11501,  -- Hmmm...wait, you aren't a moogle!
        YOU_SHOW_THE_MOOGLE_YOUR                                               = 11502,  -- @You show the moogle your %.
        LET_ME_TAKE_A_LOOK_AT_THAT_KUPO                                        = 11503,  -- Let me take a look at that, kupo.
        ID_11504                                                               = 11504,  -- ...
        HMM                                                                    = 11505,  -- Hmm...
        AN_EMPYREAN_WEAPON                                                     = 11506,  -- An...empyrean weapon?
        NO_A_MOG_BONANZA_WEAPON                                                = 11507,  -- No...a Mog Bonanza weapon...
        AND_THE_CRYSTALLIZATION_IS_IMPRESSIVE_KUPO                             = 11508,  -- And the crystallization is impressive, kupo!
        KUPOFRIED_TRULY_IS_A_MASTER_OF_HIS_ART                                 = 11509,  -- Kupofried truly is a master of his art...but how can we use this, kupo?
